(781, 'Preparation for General Chemistry', 'The course develops critical thinking and analytic problem solving skills within a chemistry context in order to prepare students for success in college-level General Chemistry窶蚤 key gateway class required for many undergraduate majors.', 'Chemistry is about atoms and molecules and their transformations,\nand is referred to as the Central Science because it connects the\nphysical and life sciences. ﾂ�General Chemistry is your gateway into chemistry, and is\nrequired for majors in just about every field of science, technology and\nmedicine. ﾂ�General Chemistry trains students to think like scientists\nthrough the application of chemical principles to solve problems. College-level general chemistry, however, is extremely\nfast-paced, and students are faced with challenges of absorbing new chemistry\nconcepts at the same time they are applied to complex problems. The goal of\nthis class is to prepare students for success in General Chemistry by honing\ntheir chemistry problem solving skills. In this class, we will review fundamental mathematical\nskills, as well as provide strategies for general chemistry problem solving. ﾂ�Focus will be placed on selected conceptual areas of chemistry, and then delve deeply into application of these concepts to solve real-world problems. ﾂ�The class emphasizes critical thinking, solution strategies for complex chemical problems and foundational math skills. ﾂ�A goal of this course is to train students to think like scientists, and prepare them for success in university courses in science, technology engineering and mathematics. I hope that you enjoy the class!', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/chemprep', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oknSUOnjsTc', '2014-07-07', 6, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/f5/40e57083bf11e387bf6bd12e2b9dc0/logo-chemprep.jpg', 'Chem', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Rutgers the State University of New Jersey', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(782, 'Music''s Big Bang: The Genesis of Rock ''n'' Roll', 'Explores the factors 窶� musical and cultural 窶� that led to the birth of American rock ''n'' roll music in the early 1950s.', 'How did rock ''n'' roll music come to be? Join us to explore Music''s Big Bang -- how music brought to America by immigrants evolved, blended and eventually became the delectable stew that is rock ''n'' roll. \n We will see and hear the ingredients in that stew, such as blues, jazz and gospel, and explore rock ''n'' roll''s first half\n decade, roughly 1955 to 1960. We will consider cultural factors, too, including the advance of technology, the migration of rural Americans from the South to the cities of the North, and the threats to mainstream American\n values presented by teenage rebellion and the Civil Rights Movement.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/musicsbigbang', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=274s1Z7KoT0', '2014-03-13', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/34/a19a110d0a59a66d90ecb8001b092e/MBB_header_04.jpg', 'Music', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Florida', '2015-11-21 09:19:33'),
(783, 'Sustainable Agricultural Land Management', 'This course will cover the agricultural and urban water quality issues in Florida, their bases, land and nutrient management strategies, and the science and policy behind the best management practices (BMPs).  Students will learn to evaluate BMP research and analyze its role in determining practices and policies that protect water quality.', 'Protecting the state窶冱 water from nutrient contamination depends on adopting best management practices (BMPs) for land and nutrient management in the urban and agricultural settings.ﾂ� BMPs must be based on science and be practical and economical to adopt, while meeting society窶冱 needs.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/sustainableag', 'N/A', '2015-03-02', 9, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/6d/040f3e75d29cf168777a3c2f4228d3/Sustainable-Agriculture.jpg', 'Bus & Mngmt, Nutrit', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Florida', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(784, 'Scaling operations: Linking strategy and execution', 'Over the past several decades, operations strategy has played an increasingly important role in business窶� success. In this course, we will equip you with concepts and tools to build operations in a way that not only supports your competitive strategy, but also allows you to create new opportunities in the market place.', 'Scaling operations: Linking strategy and execution is a five-week course dedicated to making strategic decisions that are grounded in operational reality. Together, we will study how to build and evaluate the 窶徙perating system窶� of the firm to maximize value. This involves tailoring the firm窶冱 operational competencies, assets, and processes to a specific business strategy. Each week, we窶冤l explore case studies, engage in discussions and examine realistic data. Thanks to our data-driven approach, you窶冤l be able to implement your learning directly into practice. At the end of this course, you窶冤l be ready to build an effective, actionable plan to scale your department or organization. This course will be part of a research study about learning and education. As part of this study, we will use student records, such as quiz scores, video consumptions, etc. All data will be de-identified and statistical procedures on the data are preformed at aggregated level. By participating in the course, you also agree to participate in the study. If students have any questions or any concerns, please contact our team throughﾂ�j-zhang@kellogg.northwestern.edu. ﾂ�Questions about your rights as a researchﾂ�participant may be directed to the Institutional Review Board (IRB) Office of Northwestern University through irb.northwestern.edu.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/scalingoperations', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4efffa004b2111e49d47899106e89984', '2016-01-11', 5, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/ab/bc88f04b1811e4b7b3612cbe9b32d7/front-cover-edited.jpg', 'Bus & Mngmt, Econ & Fin, Stats', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Northwestern University', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(785, 'Data Management for Clinical Research', 'Learn critical concepts and practical methods to support research data planning, collection, storage and dissemination.', 'This course is designed to teach important concepts related to research data planning, collection, storage and dissemination. Instructors will offer information and best-practice guidelines for 1) investigator-initiated & sponsored research studies 538) single- & multi-center studies, and 3) prospective data collection & secondary-reuse of clinical data for purposes of research. The curriculum will balance theoretical guidelines with the use of practical tools designed to assist in planning and conducting research. Real-world research examples, problem solving exercises and hands-on training will ensure students are comfortable with all concepts. ﾂ�', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/datamanagement', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HWcUCo5eZ6M', '2014-10-27', 5, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/ce/6c32f8720ec9c8cd3dac99fcc1c83b/data-sm.jpeg', 'Stats, Info, Tech', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Vanderbilt University', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(786, 'Neuroscience: Perception, Action and the Brain Capstone', 'In this capstone students will have a choice of three projects related to perception, to be completed across 6 weeks: (1) write a research proposal, (2) write a popular press article, or (3) create a video demonstration or multimedia application. ', 'After completing the three required courses in this Specialization, learners will have a good background in the overall organization and function of the human brain and how it supports visual perception, spatial processing and successful interaction with a complex world. We know participants in this Specialization come from a variety of backgrounds and are interested in applying the knowledge gained in neuroscience and perception in different ways; therefore, this final capstone project will offer three options from which to choose: (1) write a research proposal (for experimental research on perception and action) OR (2) write a popular press article (in non-technical language) that summarizes \ncurrent knowledge about a topic pertinent to perception and action OR (3) create a video demonstration or multimedia application (a virtual or real-world demonstration of how sensory signals give rise to perceptions and/or actions) We hope one of these project options will be intrinsically interesting to you, as well as guiding you to create a practical product for your future needs, such as enhancing skills in your current career area, or preparing for future career opportunities.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/neurofinalproject', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0fb5a1e0047311e587c90d7c0ba92350', '2015-08-10', 6, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/75/0227f04b2b11e482ab058538a3e39c/specialization_logo_v7.jpg', 'Bio & Life Sci, Medicine, Teach', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Duke University', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(787, 'Why We Need Psychology', 'For adults with an interest in the study of human behaviour 窶� especially those who have often considered studying psychology but who have yet to begin.   ', 'PLEASE NOTE: due to an unforeseen delay in the launch of the University of London International Programmes'' undergraduate Psychology programme, on which our Why We Need Psychology Coursera MOOC is based, we will not be able to launch this MOOC as planned in 2013. ﾂ� We will announce a confirmed launch date as soon as we can: if you are already registered for this course, you will be notified once a new date has been announced; if you have yet to register, feel free to click the 窶和dd to watchlist窶� button above this message to receive a notification. This course will introduce students to the discipline of psychology: in particular to the main schools of thought employed to explain human behaviour and to the potential applications of psychology in practice.ﾂ�', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/needpsych', 'N/A', '2021-01-01', 0, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/15/9dd580d5f364063fd94288be8c398a/V-multicoloured-brain.jpg', 'Humanities', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of London', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(788, 'The Camera Never Lies', 'Film, images & historical interpretation in the 20th century for those who have a general interest in history that draws on photojournalism as primary evidence, and films based on historical events.', 'This short history course is an introduction to use of\nimages and other media as historical evidence in the twentieth century, issues\nof authenticity and manipulation, and the place of film and historical\nadoptions as public history.\n\n', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/lyingcamera', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g_jMGNos7wQ', '2015-06-22', 6, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/46/fb5637e5b6d4e71b0b97cfeb0aec55/Flag-raising-on-Iwo-Jima.jpg', 'Humanities , Music', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of London', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(789, 'Career 911: Your Future Job in Medicine and Healthcare', 'This course aims to help high school students, recent graduates, and those considering career transitions explore health care career options and learn strategies for entry into the health care workforce and health related fields.', 'There are lots of amazing job opportunities inﾂ�medicine and healthcare! Join\nus, as we share the strategies and secrets for getting those jobs. This course will introduce you to healthcare professions, help you map a path\ntowards a health career, andﾂ�impart skills relevant for any career,\nincluding: articulating your personal story, resume and cover letter writing,\njob search, interviewing, professional networking, and professional\ncommunications. In this course, you will hear theﾂ�personal stories, experiences,ﾂ�and journeys of dozens of people who work in health related careers. You will also have the opportunity to connect with a supportive community of students, mentors, and health care professionals to explore your interests, find resources, and discover exciting new opportunities. The course features more than 50 different guests and lecturers, including Northwestern University faculty from Feinberg School of Medicine; the Kellogg School of Management; the Medill School of Journalism, Media, Integrated Marketing Communications; the School of Professional Studies; Weinberg College of Arts and Sciences; and the School of Communication. The course is also a resource and tool through which educators, parents, career counselors and others can support students窶� career readiness and professional advancement.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/healthcarejobs', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4a4a08c0607a11e4b1e0638b207644d9', '2015-09-21', 6, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/3e/3d4f004b3611e4a6ecc96192f648b7/HCMOOC_Courselogo.JPG', 'Education, Bus & Mngmt, Medicine, Health', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Northwestern University', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(790, 'English Common Law: Structure and Principles', 'For anyone with an interest in learning about one of the oldest and most influential legal systems in the world.', 'The\nCommon Law of England and Wales is one of the major global\nlegal traditions. In order to understand the common law, we need to deal with\nits history, and the development of its characteristic institutions like the\njury, judge made law, parliamentary sovereignty and due process. We also need\nto ask some critical questions. What role does democracy\nplay in the development of the common law? To what extent are human rights\ncentral to the modern common law? How does the common law of England and Wales\nrelate to the law of the European Union? Answering these questions will give us\ninsights into the current challenges the law faces\nand its possible futures.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/engcomlaw', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9872e8f0dcd111e388eb4f30d1043e5b', '2015-07-06', 6, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/dc/7e695f3864e8bdd71714c0abc22e58/new-logo.jpg', 'Humanities , Law', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of London', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(791, 'Online Games: Literature, New Media, and Narrative', 'Focused on Tolkien and The Lord of the Rings Online, this course explores what happens to stories and films when they are turned into online games.', 'Intended for both newcomers who are\ncurious about video games and experienced gamers who want to reflect on their\npassion, this course will explore what happens to stories, paintings, and films\nwhen they become the basis of massively multiplayer online games.ﾂ� The\nLord of the Rings trilogy窶杯he novels, films, and video game窶蚤re our central\nexample of how 窶徨emediation窶� transforms familiar stories as they move across\nmedia.ﾂ� The course is\ndesigned as a university-level English literature class窶蚤 multi-genre,\nmultimedia tour of how literature, film, and games engage in the basic human\nactivity of storytelling.ﾂ� Our journey\nwill enable us to learn something about narrative theory, introduce us to some\nkey topics in media studies and cover some of the history and theory of video\ngames.ﾂ� It will also take us to some\nlandmarks of romance literature, the neverending story that lies behind most\nfantasy games: J.R.R. Tolkien窶冱 The\nFellowship of the Ring, a bit of Edmund Spenser窶冱 Faerie Queene, and poems by Keats, Tennyson, Browning, and others.\n\n Drawing on centuries\nof romance narrative conventions, the twenty-first century gaming industry has\nbecome a creative and economic powerhouse.ﾂ�\nIt engages the talents of some of our brightest writers, artists,\ncomposers, computer engineers, game theorists, video producers, and marketing\nprofessionals, and in 2012, it generated an estimated $64 billion in revenue.ﾂ� Anyone interested in today窶冱 culture needs to\nbe conversant with the ways this new medium is altering our understanding of\nstories.ﾂ� Join me as we set out on an\nintellectual adventure, the quest to discover the cultural heritage of online\ngames. Reviews of the last offering: http://penny-arcade.com/report/article/why-40000-students-from-around-the-world-have-signed-up-to-st... http://inventorspot.com/articles/gaming_lotr_and_new_media_interview_professor_jay_clayton', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/onlinegames', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W-FkXWzPrXw', '2015-04-27', 7, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/12/c22bb29b7a6b73d60eba57bf0fe152/Cheeryble-by-moonlight.jpg', 'Humanities , Arts', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Vanderbilt University', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(792, 'Fog Networks and the Internet of Things', 'This course teaches the fundamentals of Fog Networking, the network architecture that uses one or a collaborative multitude of end-user clients or near-user edge devices to carry out storage, communication, computation, and control in a network. It also teaches the key results in the design of the Internet of Things, including consumer and industrial applications. ', 'Pushing computation, control and storage into the 窶彡loud窶� has been a key trend in\nnetworking in the past decade. The cloud is now 窶彭escending窶� to the network\nedge and often diffused among the client devices in both mobile and wireline\nnetworks. The cloud is becoming the 窶彷og.窶� Empowered by the latest chips,\nradios, and sensors, each client device today is powerful in computation, in\nstorage, in sensing and in communication. Yet client devices are still limited\nin battery power, global view of the network, and mobility support. Most\ninterestingly, the collection of many clients in a crowd presents a highly\ndistributed, under-organized, and possibly dense network. \n\n Fog Networking is an architecture that will also support the Internet of Things, IoT, such as the 窶彡onnected wearables.窶� Bold, new user interfaces are getting close to affordable price points for the mass, begging questions on the 窶彗rchitectural choices for the glasses and watches,窶� from naming to billing, and from session management to resource optimization. Fog Networking leverages past experience in sensor networks, P2P and MANET research, and incorporates the latest advances in devices, network systems, and data science to reshape the 窶彙alance of power窶� in the ecosystem of computing and networking.ﾂ�', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/fog', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3bb8291053ad11e49b9ba916b58830db', '2015-03-02', 6, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/5e/4244604d6e11e49ba297232d865156/fog-logo.png', 'ComSci: SE, Engi', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Princeton University', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(793, 'Cloud Networking', 'The network is what makes the cloud. The cloud窶冱 key capabilities窶杯he ability to share infrastructure, the ability to move and scale applications across servers, massive parallelism, virtualization, and worldwide connectivity窶蚤re all rooted in the network. Learn how it all works!', 'In the cloud networking course, we will see what the network needs to do to enable cloud computing. We will explore current practice by talking to leading industry experts, as well as looking into interesting new research that might shape the cloud network窶冱 future.\n\n This course will allow us to explore in-depth the challenges for cloud networking窶派ow do we build a network infrastructure that provides the agility to deploy virtual networks on a shared infrastructure, that enables both efficient transfer of big data and low latency communication, and that enables applications to be federated across countries and continents? Examining how these objectives are met will set the stage for the rest of the course. \n\n This course places an emphasis on both operations and design rationale窶琶.e., how things work and why they were designed this way. We''re excited to start the course with you and take a look inside what has become the critical communications infrastructure for many applications today.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/cloudnetworking', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=524dc990533111e4a145035351c7e2c6', '2015-11-02', 5, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/13/360da0530c11e492408bf1c99cee22/cloud_networking_v01_600X340.jpg', 'ComSci: Systems & Security', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(794, 'Economic Issues, Food & You', 'This course emphasizes the role of economics regarding its influence on food prices, the environment, and government policies. The primary objective of this course is to explore the basic tool kit of economic concepts that will enable students to critically analyze the choices they face as consumers and world citizens.', 'Students will study the economic concepts of scarcity, supply and demand, society窶冱 income and well-being, inflation, productivity, unemployment, the basic tools of finance, labor, and the 窶廡ed窶�.ﾂ� Students will examine how parts of the U.S. economy function and develop an awareness of current economic issues and problems.ﾂ�', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/ecfoodandyou', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Tn_f7C7hZKE', '2013-09-09', 10, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/f7/ee7c21aad1a240a7de4f4201cb2c9c/Eco-Issues-Food-and-You.jpeg', 'Econ & Fin, Nutrit', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Florida', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(795, 'Introduction aux droits de l窶冑omme', 'Ce cours propose une introduction ﾃ� la protection internationale des droits de l窶冑omme. Il en prﾃｩsente les sources, les catﾃｩgories, le contenu et les limites qui leur sont opposables, ainsi que les obligations qu窶冓ls gﾃｩnﾃｨrent ﾃ� la charge des Etats. Il expose aussi les principaux mﾃｩcanismes de mise en ﾅ砥vre prﾃｩvus au niveau universel et rﾃｩgional pour assurer leur respect.', 'Depuis la fin de la Seconde Guerre mondiale, les\n droits de l窶冑omme sont un domaine en plein essor. De nombreuses causes\n sont aujourd窶冑ui dﾃｩfendues et dﾃｩbattues sous la banniﾃｨre des droits de\n l窶冑ommeﾂ�: la protection des minoritﾃｩs, la lutte contre la\n discrimination des femmes, des personnes lesbiennes, gaies, bisexuelles\n et transgenres (LGBT), la lutte contre la torture et les disparitions\n forcﾃｩes, la lutte contre la pauvretﾃｩ ou encore la protection de\n l窶册nvironnement et la protection des donnﾃｩes. Partout dans le monde, ces\n causes mobilisent tant les acteurs politiques que la sociﾃｩtﾃｩ civile et elles sont\n discutﾃｩes dans de multiples enceintes, nationales et internationales. Le prﾃｩsent cours vise ﾃ� offrir les bases nﾃｩcessaires\n pour apprﾃｩhender et comprendre le domaine vaste et complexe que sont\n devenus les droits de l窶冑omme. Quelles sont les caractﾃｩristiques et les\n diffﾃｩrentes catﾃｩgorie des droits de l窶冑ommeﾂ�? Quels sont leurs fondements\n philosophiques et historiques ? Pourquoi ces droits sont-ils\n importantsﾂ�? Quels instruments visent ﾃ� les protﾃｩger ? Comment\n rendre ces droits opﾃｩrationnelsﾂ�? Quels mﾃｩcanismes existent pour les\n mettre en ﾅ砥vre et quels sont leurs avantages et leurs\n inconvﾃｩnientsﾂ�? En abordant ces questions, le cours s窶兮dresse tant ﾃ�\n des membres de la communautﾃｩ universitaire qu窶凖� des praticiens\n (responsables politiques, membres du corps diplomatique, fonctionnaires,\n journalistes, membres d窶儖NG, dﾃｩfenseurs des droits de l窶冑omme et\n spﾃｩcialistes de la coopﾃｩration au dﾃｩveloppement, de l窶兮ide humanitaire et\n des questions relatives aux rﾃｩfugiﾃｩs), ainsi qu窶凖� toutes les personnes\n qui sont engagﾃｩes dans la protection des droits de l窶冑omme ou simplement\n dﾃｩsireuses de mieux comprendre ce phﾃｩnomﾃｨne. Le cours est conﾃｧu et dispensﾃｩ par les Professeurs\n Maya Hertig Randall et Michel Hottelier, de la Facultﾃｩ de droit de\n l窶儷niversitﾃｩ de Genﾃｨve. Durant le cours, des membres d窶冩rganes et\n institutions vouﾃｩs ﾃ� la protection des droits de l窶冑omme et des\n spﾃｩcialistes de la communautﾃｩ acadﾃｩmique seront invitﾃｩs ﾃ� intervenir. \n\n\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/droitshomme', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vF6rCfxP6zA', '2015-02-09', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/3a/c149c44a09ec65c906ec6c66e03595/logo_Droits_Homme.jpg', 'Humanities , Law', 'Coursera', 0, 'French', 'yes', 'University of Geneva', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
