(928, 'Introduction to Computational Arts: Visual Arts', 'This production class serves as an introduction to, and exploration of digital imagery in the arts. Lectures will cover concepts and presentations of artists working in various capacities with computers, as well as tutorials on specific software packages. ', 'In this 5-week course we窶冤l introduce the fundamentals of computational arts窶田overing basic programming, simple image processing and elementary sound recording. This class has been taught for seventeen years at Stony Brook University, and is an accessible introduction to combining arts and computing. We will cover Photoshop CS5 and GIMP, which is a free open-source tool offering the same functionality as Photoshop. Whether you have access to one or the other, you will learn how to create and manipulate digital images, and most importantly, you will become comfortable enough to expand on what you learn here, after the end of our course. You will complete both technical assignments and artistic projects, and learn how to participate in an aesthetic critique. You will be exposed to historical works of art from the 20th and 21st centuries which will offer you a context for your artistic endeavors. Peer review is integral to the success of this class; we will also teach you how to give constructive criticism. By the end of the 5 weeks you should have a strong foundation on how to use computers for image manipulation, and expression of your artistic ideas. Additionally, you窶冤l create an online portfolio of your digital art projects, and be able to communicate ideas about art. ﾂ� Each week you窶冤l watch two video series - one on the theory and one on the practice. There will be technical assignments and artistic projects which will be peer reviewed. We窶决e looking forward to working with you.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/compartsvisual', 'N/A', '2014-03-03', 6, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/3a/b34430900511e3b02ec5861dc1ee64/compartsvisual.png', 'Arts', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'The State University of New York', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(929, 'Introduction to Computational Arts: Audio', 'In this 6-week course we窶冤l introduce the fundamentals of digital audio. The course will provide the essentials of recording and editing sound, and culminates with a piece using both recorded and synthesized sound. ', 'In this 5-week course we窶冤l introduce the fundamentals of digital audio. This is the final third of a class which has been taught for seventeen years at Stony Brook University, and is an accessible introduction to combining arts and computing. The other two portions have already been taught this spring, but we will offer them again in the fall: ﾂ� Introduction to Computational Arts: Image Manipulation and Introduction to Computational Arts: Processing. For sound we窶冤l be Logic or a combination of Audacity and Soundation. Students can use other Digital Audio Workstations such as Reaper or Ableton Live. The course will provide the essentials of digital audioﾂ�and culminates with a piece using both recorded and synthesized sound.ﾂ� You will complete both technical assignments and an artistic project, and learn how to participate in an aesthetic critique. This course is more about recording and sound art than about writing traditional music - I will give examples of work which doesn''t require a background in traditional music to create.ﾂ� Peer review is integral to the success of this class; we will also teach you how to give constructive criticism. By the end of the 5 weeks you should have a strong foundation for how computers work and deal with audio. Additionally, you窶冤l create an online portfolio of digital sound projects, and be able to communicate ideas about aesthetics. ﾂ� Each week you窶冤l watch two video series - one on the theory and one on the practice. The practice videos are divided by software platforms. ﾂ�There will be technical assignments and artistic projects which will be peer reviewed. We窶决e looking forward to working with you.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/compartsaudio', 'N/A', '2014-04-14', 6, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/1e/e2ea70b52211e3b1511397deeef4f6/compartsaudio.png', 'Music', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'The State University of New York', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(930, 'Fundamentos de la escritura en espaﾃｱol', 'Curso bﾃ｡sico de espaﾃｱol que proporciona las herramientas lingﾃｼﾃｭsticas necesarias para un manejo efectivo de la lengua escrita.', 'La\nestructura interna del curso estﾃ｡ conformada de contenidos de ortografﾃｭa y\nredacciﾃｳn. En la primera parte, se estudiarﾃ｡ todo lo referente a la\nacentuaciﾃｳn: divisiﾃｳn silﾃ｡bica, regla general, hiatos y diptongos. Una vez\nreforzados estos conocimientos se revisarﾃ｡ lo referente al acento diacrﾃｭtico y\nlos casos especiales. Ademﾃ｡s, se estudiarﾃ｡ la estructura de la oraciﾃｳn; se revisarﾃ｡n las\ncaracterﾃｭsticas de la oraciﾃｳn simple y compuesta y se estudiarﾃ｡n las oraciones\nsubordinadas adjetivas, sustantivas, adverbiales y las oraciones coordinadas. Posteriormente se abordarﾃ｡n temas referentes a las grafﾃｭas. Se\nanalizarﾃ｡n los usos principales de b/v, g/j, y/ll, ﾂ�y c/z/s y el uso de\nmayﾃｺsculas y minﾃｺsculas. En cuanto a los signos de puntuaciﾃｳn se estudiarﾃ｡n los usos\nprincipales del punto, coma, punto y coma y dos puntos. Se explicarﾃ｡n las\nreglas mﾃ｡s importantes de cada uno de estos, con ejemplos. Asﾃｭ\nmismo, se estudiarﾃ｡ la conformaciﾃｳn del pﾃ｡rrafo y se practicarﾃ｡n estrategias\npara la construcciﾃｳn de pﾃ｡rrafos descriptivos, narrativos, argumentativos, de clasificaciﾃｳn, de proceso, de causa y efecto\ny de comparaciﾃｳn y contraste. En la ﾃｺltima parte, se revisarﾃ｡n las caracterﾃｭsticas del texto\npara que puedas construir textos bien estructurados. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n Con este\nprograma, el participante elaborarﾃ｡ escritos en los que sea evidente la\ncorrecta construcciﾃｳn de oraciones y pﾃ｡rrafos.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/escrituraesp', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q96LwAEzmwo', '2014-08-11', 7, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/c3/709da0943211e38708bf81bc7d7885/Fundamentos.png', 'Education, SocSci, Humanities', 'Coursera', 0, 'Spanish', 'yes', 'Tecnolﾃｳgico de Monterrey', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(931, 'Exploring Neural Data', 'Try your hand at understanding the brain by learning to analyze neural data yourself!  Working with real neural data sets from neuroscience research labs, you窶冤l learn data analysis techniques so you can discover for yourself how the brain works.', 'Exploring Neural Data is an opportunity to learn about neuroscience research and explore questions related to how brains work. It is an introductory level course designed to help you understand the real-life challenges faced by neuroscientists as they work with the large amount of data they collect from the brain. Leading neuroscientists will give tours of their labs, describe their research, and explain their data analytic techniques. You will have the chance to explore actual data collected in these researchers'' labs. Throughout the course, you will gain knowledge in three main areas: basic principles of neuroscience and questions driving research in this field; programming with the open-source language Python; and essential techniques for data analysis. We will begin by exploring single neurons, then turn our attention to multiple neurons, and finally consider tools that sample from tens of thousands of neurons. At the end of the class, you will have the opportunity to investigate in detail a data set of your choice provided by one of the researchers whose work you''ve learned about.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/neuraldata', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7ef65000d7b911e3b77f4b82b4c7c601', '2014-09-29', 10, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/0f/c84890d21f11e39b0b2180ed97d159/Exploring_Neural_Data_logo.png', 'Bio & Life Sci, Stats', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Brown University', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(932, 'The American Disease: Drugs and Drug Control in the USA', 'This online course introduces the history and practice of drug policy. Students will learn about drug laws and their origins, and the complex task of drug policy analysis. The course also tackles contemporary issues in drug control, such as marijuana policy and prescription drug misuse.', 'This online course introduces the history and practice of drug policy. Students will learn about drug laws and their origins, and the complex task of drug policy analysis. The course also tackles contemporary issues in drug control, such as marijuana policy and prescription drug misuse.ﾂ�At the completion of this course, students should be able to: Discuss federal and state responses to drugs from the late 1800s to the present Compare pre-and post-Nixon-era drug policy Analyze drug policies to determine how well they advance stated goals Describe how processes in the brain are affected by drug use and addiction', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/americandisease', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0aUSOqRHfDM', '2014-07-14', 10, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/cb/0dda30ba8b11e3a65f511453b70f22/drug-policy_final-01-_2__.jpg', 'Medicine, Health', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Florida', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(933, 'Pensamiento algorﾃｭtmico', 'ﾂｿQuﾃｩ es un algoritmo? ﾂｿCﾃｳmo se hace un diagrama de flujo? ﾂｿQuﾃｩ es un pseudocﾃｳdigo? ﾂｿCﾃｳmo me pueden ayudar a resolver problemas cotidianos?\n\nEste curso bﾃ｡sico de computaciﾃｳn te ayudarﾃ｡ a desarrollar el pensamiento algorﾃｭtmico necesario para solucionar problemas en forma estructurada.', 'ﾂｿHas tenido que resolver un mismo problema varias veces?, por ejemplo, al salir de viaje o preparar una reuniﾃｳn con amigos. Y cada vez, ﾂｿtuviste que volver a pensar en todo lo que hay que hacer, cuﾃ｡les pasos y en quﾃｩ orden? Precisamente lo que busca este curso es proporcionarte las herramientas necesarias con las que identificarﾃ｡s, analizarﾃ｡s y plantearﾃ｡s soluciones efectivas para estas situaciones. Asﾃｭ, al encontrarte con el mismo problema, ya sabrﾃ｡s una manera de resolverlo. En este curso introductorio a la computaciﾃｳn, desarrollarﾃ｡s el razonamiento estructurado necesario para analizar problemas bﾃ｡sicos y resolverlos utilizando la reflexiﾃｳn lﾃｳgica y el pensamiento algorﾃｭtmico. De igual manera, reconocerﾃ｡s los elementos que estﾃ｡n a tu alcance y cﾃｳmo los puedes utilizar efectivamente para lograr tus objetivos.Al finalizar el curso, aprenderﾃ｡s a plasmar soluciones en tﾃｩrminos computacionales a travﾃｩs de diagramas de flujo o pseudocﾃｳdigo. Ademﾃ｡s, podrﾃ｡s trasladar estas soluciones a herramientas como hojas de cﾃ｡lculo que te serﾃ｡n ﾃｺtiles en tus actividades diarias, personales y profesionales.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/pealgoritmico', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GpV-4QGYfjI', '2014-10-20', 6, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/46/bcef2098b011e38668c30646c6ded3/computacion5.png', 'Education, ComSci: Theory', 'Coursera', 0, 'Spanish', 'yes', 'Tecnolﾃｳgico de Monterrey', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(934, 'Tropical Parasitology: Protozoans, Worms, Vectors and Human Diseases', 'This course provides students an understanding of important human parasitic diseases, including their life cycles, vectors of transmission, distribution and epidemiology, pathophysiology and clinical manifestations, treatment, and prevention and control.  ', '"Tropical Parasitology: Protozoans, Worms, Vectors and Human Diseases" will present information on important human parasites. The specific parasites for discussion include malaria, trypanosomiasis, toxoplasmosis, cestodes (Taenia saginata, Taenia solium, and Echinococcus), trematodes (Schistosoma and Fasciola), nematodes (Ancylostoma/Necator, Strongyloides, filariasis, and Ascaris), and ectoparasites. An emphasis will be placed on field demonstrations of relevance in sub-Saharan Africa and clinical presentations of parasitic illness, including their life cycles, vectors of transmission, distribution and \nepidemiology, pathophysiology and clinical manifestations, treatment, \nand prevention and control.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/parasitology', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ef7d82709b4b11e49cd8eda9642f9b5c', '2016-01-11', 10, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/dc/cff820308811e4ad70e73b06f30e11/ParaLogo.png', 'Medicine, Health', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Duke University, null', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(935, 'The Role of the Renminbi in the International Monetary System ', 'This course will discuss various aspects of the Renminbi internationalization, including the reform of the international monetary system, the opportunities and challenges to internationalize the Renminbi, the evolution of China''s monetary and exchange rate policies, and the implications of the Renminbi internationalization for Hong Kong.', 'The current international\nmonetary system has critical defects. An effective reform of the system calls\nfor a new international currency, for which the Renminbi may be a promising\ncandidate. Despite the rapid growth of the Chinese economy, certain prerequisites\nhave to be satisfied before the Renminbi can be internationalized. China needs\nto ensure full convertibility of the Renminbi and further develop its financial\nmarkets to facilitate the process of internationalization.\n\n This course will discuss various\naspects of the Renminbi internationalization. Specifically, innovative\nsuggestions will be provided on topics including the reform of the\ninternational monetary system, the opportunities and challenges of the Renminbi\ninternationalization, and the evolution of China窶冱 monetary and exchange rate\npolicies. Since the internationalization of Renminbi is important to the future\nof Hong Kong as an international financial center, the lectures will also\ndiscuss the possible implications of this process for Hong Kong.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/renminbi', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KjtcIrDKUo0', '2013-09-30', 4, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/43/f60d61a66e46088b54c1384cb69619/renminbi.jpg', 'Econ & Fin', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'The Chinese University of Hong Kong', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(936, 'Massively Multivariable Open Online Calculus Course', 'M2O2C2 provides a first taste of multivariable differential calculus.\nBy introducing the machinery of linear algebra, this course provides helpful tools for understanding the derivative of a function of many variables.', 'M2O2C2 is an invitation to think carefully about how one thing changingﾂ�affects something else. What is the "derivative" of a function of manyﾂ�variables? How can a curved object be approximated by a flat plane? Whatﾂ�does the chain rule look like when many things are affecting many otherﾂ�things? How do we find an input which maximizes a function of manyﾂ�variables? This is a first course in multivariable differential calculus, but alongﾂ�the way, we will also introduce a ton of linear algebra. The result is aﾂ�course targeted at a student who has seen a bit of calculus and who isﾂ�willing to learn about linear transformationsﾂ�and vectors; such aﾂ�student will have the best possible vantage point from which to exploreﾂ�derivatives of functions of many variables.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/m2o2c2', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-EA7MOco3M4', '2014-03-14', 6, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/1f/b5be70959f11e3ba1e97f03601e90c/logo.png', 'Math', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'The Ohio State University', '2015-11-21 09:19:33'),
(937, 'Forests and Humans: From the Midwest to Madagascar', 'Explore the forests of the world, from the taiga to the tropical rainforest! Learn why humans depend on them, and how we can sustainably manage forests for us and the many species with whom we share them.', 'Did you know that thousands of people could have been saved during the 2009 tsunami if mangrove forests had been protected窶ｦ and that the boreal forest holds 40% of the Earth窶冱 soil carbon窶ｦ and that only 7% of forests are 窶徨ain forest,窶� but this biome holds 50% of the world窶冱 species? Did you hear that big cities like New York and Quito are mandating forest protection to save their city''s water supply? This is only a handful of the questions you窶冤l find answers to in this Forests and Humans online course. This course provides an overview of the geography, ecology, and economic importance of the world窶冱 forest biomes. You窶冤l learn how climate influences vegetation and, in-turn, how forests impact global climate. You窶冤l meet scientists working to understand the astounding biodiversity and ecological complexity of forest ecosystems, and how these ecosystems support human life. We窶冤l discuss the threats to forest ecosystems around the world, and hear from the people trying to protect them. The course emphasizes the forest resources and services that humans depend upon, and how we can maintain these resources into the future. We窶冤l analyze the idea of 窶徭ustainability窶� when it comes to forest management, hear alternative viewpoints about what this word means, and discuss potential conflicts. Finally, we窶冤l take a look at the many real-world programs in place at the global, national, and local level to sustainably manage forests.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/forestshumans', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ab3a9f200a2d11e5b32f13dc7596323e', '2015-09-30', 4, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/50/7f9b60609211e5b574efb36d546400/pacificNW-old-growth-hiking2OR.jpg', 'Bio & Life Sci, Energy & Earth Sci, EarthSci', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Wisconsin窶溺adison', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(938, 'Information Theory', 'This course is an introduction to information theory, which emphasizes fundamental concepts as well as analytical techniques. Specific topics include: Information Measures, The I-Measure, Zero-Error Data Compression, Weak Typicality, Strong Typicality, Discrete Memoryless Channels, etc.', 'The lectures are based on the first 11 chapters of Prof. Raymond Yeung窶冱 textbook entitled Information Theory and Network Coding (Springer 2008). \n\n Chapter 1 The Science of Informationﾂ� Chapter 2 Information Measuresﾂ� Chapter 3ﾂ�The I-Measureﾂ� Chapter 4 Zero-Error Data Compressionﾂ� Chapter 5 Weak Typicalityﾂ� Chapter 6ﾂ�Strong Typicalityﾂ� Chapter 7 Discrete Memoryless Channelsﾂ� Chapter 8 Rate-Distortion Theoryﾂ� Chapter 9 The Blahut-Arimoto Algorithmsﾂ� Chapter 10 Differential Entropyﾂ� Chapter 11 Continuous-Valued Channels\nThis book and its predecessor,ﾂ�A First Course in Information Theoryﾂ�(Kluwer 2002,\nessentially the first edition of the 2008 book), have been adopted by over 60\nuniversities around the world as either a textbook or reference text. The electronic version\nof the 2008 book can be downloaded for free (with institutional subscription). At the completion of this course, the student should be able to: Demonstrate knowledge and understanding of the fundamentals of information theory. Appreciate the notion of fundamental limits in communication systems and more generally all systems. Develop deeper understanding of communication systems. Apply the concepts of information theory to various disciplines in information science.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/informationtheory', 'N/A', '2015-01-05', 18, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/ec/bba7bbae6eac875e7231f6cc6523dc/informationtheory.jpg', 'Info, Tech', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'The Chinese University of Hong Kong', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(939, 'Case Studies in Personalized Medicine', 'Learn how advances in biomedicine hold the potential to revolutionize drug development, drug treatments, and disease prevention: where are we now, and what does the future hold? This course is intended for healthcare providers 5+ years out of training--a lot has changed!! Other providers, medical/health sciences students, and members of the public may also be interested. ', 'Doctors have been personalizing care for patients since the time\nof Hippocrates 窶� we know that not every patient derives benefit from drug\ntreatments and that side effects are common with almost any treatment.ﾂ� Studies in the mid-20th century\nbegan to identify the basis of variability in response to drug treatments, and\nin particular the role of genetic factors in that variability.ﾂ� With the development of new technologies to\nunderstand human genetic diversity has come the opportunity to identify how\ncertain diseases run in families and why some patients respond very well to drug\ntreatment while others develop catastrophic side effects. This understanding presents the possibility of developing new\ndrugs targeting specific molecular and genetic mechanisms of disease.ﾂ� \n\n This course will present short primers in genetics and mechanisms\nunderlying variability in drug responses. A series of case studies will be used\nto illustrate principles of how genetics are being brought to bear on refining\ndiagnoses and on personalizing treatment in rare and common diseases. The ethical\nand operational issues around how to implement large scale genomic sequencing\nin clinical practice will be addressed.ﾂ�\n This course is intended for working healthcare professionals. Other providers, medical and other students, and members of the public may also be interested.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/personalizedmed', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=59e69670e38f11e48b02f3672e69d4bc', '2021-01-01', 0, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/d1/6463a059fe11e4b597ed1590634d22/Course_ImageV2.png', 'Bio & Life Sci, Medicine, Health', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Vanderbilt University', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(940, 'Tecnologﾃｭas de informaciﾃｳn y comunicaciﾃｳn en la educaciﾃｳn', 'Analizar diferentes casos de estudio de usos educativos de las TIC y diseﾃｱa un ambiente de aprendizaje que involucre herramientas digitales y tecnologﾃｭas basadas en Internet. ', 'Las tecnologﾃｭas de informaciﾃｳn y comunicaciﾃｳn (TIC) han transformado la educaciﾃｳn. Ello ocurre no sﾃｳlo porque ﾃｩstas han facilitado el desarrollo de algunas tareas que comﾃｺnmente realizﾃ｡bamos los profesores, los alumnos y los administradores sino porque tambiﾃｩn han abierto oportunidades para modificar tanto los ambientes de aprendizaje en los cuales se llevan a cabo los procesos educativos asﾃｭ como los mﾃｩtodos empleados para enseﾃｱar y aprender e incluso, cambiar los roles que anteriormente jugaba cada uno de los actores que intervenimos en el proceso educativo. ﾂ�A lo largo de este curso analizaremos diferentes ambientes de aprendizaje y el papel que juegan las TIC en cada uno de ellos; reflexionando especﾃｭficamente acerca de aquellos que podemos desarrollar nosotros mismos dados los contextos personales en los que nos encontramos. El curso se imparte en espaﾃｱol.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/ticyeducacion', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ehGPilntzrs', '2014-03-03', 5, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/2b/bc2872519870dbd473e9d42d789104/20130214.logo.curso.tic.en.educacin.jpg', 'Education', 'Coursera', 0, 'Spanish', 'yes', 'Universidad Nacional Autﾃｳnoma de Mﾃｩxico', '2015-11-21 09:19:33'),
(941, 'Audio Signal Processing for Music Applications', 'In this course you will learn about audio signal processing methodologies that are specific for music and of use in real applications. You will learn to analyse, synthesize and transform sounds using the Python programming language.', 'Audio signal processing is an engineering field that focuses on the computational methods for intentionally altering sounds, methods that are used in many musical applications. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n We have put together a course that can be of\ninterest and accessible to people coming from diverse backgrounds while going\ndeep into several signal processing topics. We focus on a number of spectral processing\ntechniques of relevance for the description and transformation of sounds, developing the basic theoretical and practical knowledge with which to analyze,\nsynthesize, transform and describe audio signals in the context of music\napplications. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n The course is based on open software and content. The\ndemonstrations and programming exercises are done using Python under Ubuntu,\nand the references and materials for the course come from open online\nrepositories. We are also distributing with open licensesﾂ�the software and\nmaterials developed for the course.\n\n', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/audio', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ffe1f410471d11e5aa2df90302bab285', '2015-09-21', 10, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/46/a24e201eea11e4815a1db9e87d56ee/figure.png', 'Music, Info, Tech, Engi', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Stanford University, null', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(942, 'Introduction to Light, Color, and Life', 'To share knowledge and issues in the physical properties of light, the accommodation of light in biological phenomena and medical applications, and the dynamic ways that light is experienced through color in everyday life. \n', 'This course deals with various topics in light, color, and life, and teaches students certain expertise in the physical properties of light, the accommodation of light in biological phenomena and medical applications, and the dynamic ways that light is experienced through color in everyday life. Through the convergence of diverse knowledge, creative research topics will be explored and interdisciplinary inquiries that show most potential and professionalism will be further studied.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/lcl', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6Ai09GV5Dw8', '2014-05-26', 6, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/97/fea520983a11e39572a90add39288e/logo1.jpg', 'Bio & Life Sci, EarthSci, Info, Tech', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Korea Advanced Institute of Science and Technology', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(943, 'C++ For C Programmers', 'This course is for experienced C programmers who want to program in C++. The examples and exercises require a basic understanding of algorithms and object-oriented software.', 'The course provides an overview of C++ for the experienced C programmer. You will learn how C++ is more powerful than C. The C++ STL library will be featured. This library allows C++ programmers to code generically, efficiently and at a high level. You will learn how to write basic graph algorithms such as the shortest path algorithm. You''ll then put this skill to use in a programming assignment aimed at producing an intelligent hex player.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/cplusplus4c', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tph2O4qPNMg', '2013-10-14', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/5a/9714c78f48e904da8812795fe243c9/Cplusplus_pic.jpg', 'ComSci: SE', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of California, Santa Cruz', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(944, 'Children Acquiring Literacy Naturally', 'This course will survey fundamental principles of language acquisition and learning to read. We will explore the possibility of becoming literate without formal schooling and instruction. No prior background in behavioral science, neuroscience, or technology is required.', 'Have recent developments in behavioral\nscience, neuroscience, and technology made it possibleﾂ�to achieve universal literacy with minimal cost? This course explores that important question.ﾂ�The lectures contemplate a revolutionary\nnew age that challenges the survival of our educational institutions and\nsociety as we know them. Learn about current research and theory in language\nacquisition, reading pedagogy, and wearable computing to assess the possibility\nof an interactive system that would enable infants, toddlers, and preschool children to\nacquire literacy naturally.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/childliteracy', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BVyEdK4pMTk', '2021-01-01', 0, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/a2/d2c66287ca20bc22a88b4fff39e49d/Slide1.jpg', 'Education, SocSci, Info, Tech', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of California, Santa Cruz', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
