(967, 'Initiation ﾃ� la thﾃｩorie des distributions', 'Une fonction discontinue peut-elle ﾃｪtre solution d''une ﾃｩquation diffﾃｩrentielle? Comment dﾃｩfinir rigoureusement la masse de Dirac (une "fonction" d''intﾃｩgrale un, nulle partout sauf en un point) et ses dﾃｩrivﾃｩes? Peut-on dﾃｩfinir une notion de "dﾃｩrivﾃｩe d''ordre fractionnaire"?  Cette initiation aux distributions rﾃｩpond ﾃ� ces questions - et ﾃ� bien d''autres.', 'Dans plusieurs domaines des sciences (physique, mﾃｩcanique, analyse numﾃｩrique, etc.) apparaﾃｮt la nﾃｩcessitﾃｩ de dﾃｩvelopper un calcul diffﾃｩrentiel "gﾃｩnﾃｩralisﾃｩ" pour des fonctions peu rﾃｩguliﾃｨres, par exemple discontinues. La premiﾃｨre leﾃｧon prﾃｩsente une situation de ce genre. L''objet de ce cours est d''introduire la thﾃｩorie des distributions qui fournit une rﾃｩponse ﾃｩlﾃｩgante ﾃ� ce problﾃｨme. Dans un premier temps, nous prﾃｩsentons la notion de distribution, gﾃｩnﾃｩralisant la notion de fonction, et les premiﾃｨres propriﾃｩtﾃｩs de ces objets mathﾃｩmatiques. On montre ensuite comment certaines opﾃｩrations bien connues sur les fonctions, en particulier la dﾃｩrivation, se prolongent naturellement au cadre des distributions. Le cours s''achﾃｨve sur quelques applications ﾃ� des exemples classiques d''ﾃｩquations aux dﾃｩrivﾃｩes partielles linﾃｩaires.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/distributions', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A6Fw_-WuEjw', '2015-01-19', 9, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/b6/4412c4848eaa5eb6c279cfb379698a/logg.jpg', 'Math', 'Coursera', 0, 'French', 'yes', 'ﾃ営ole Polytechnique', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(968, 'Foundations of Virtual Instruction', 'Learn what it takes to teach a K-12 course online! Investigate the history of virtual education, explore innovative tools, and examine key issues related to K-12 virtual instruction. ', 'This course provides teachers with the foundation for understanding the\nmovement towards virtual instruction. It introduces fundamental knowledge\nneeded by teachers to succeed in a technology-dependent, instructional\nenvironment. You will explore the history of online learning and understand\nhow a variety of delivery models are evolving in the K-12 environment,\nranging from completely online to hybrid or blended classrooms. We will\ndiscuss how the programs work and who they serve, addressing some basics\nabout equity issues, access and school funding, as well as ethical and\nlegal issues that support and challenge the models. Upon completion of\nthe course, you will understand what it takes to transition from teaching\nin the classroom to providing virtual instruction.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/virtualinstruction', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aJ1wJaRCcow', '2015-07-06', 5, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/4d/b82075de73b5f48912d8b387471b16/Virtual-Instruction-Logo_Correct-Size.jpg', 'Education, Teach, Info, Tech', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of California, Irvine', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(969, 'Big Data em Saﾃｺde no Brasil', 'Aprenda a utilizar as novas metodologias de big data para a anﾃ｡lise de grandes bancos de dados e para a melhoria dos processos de tomada de decisﾃ｣o.', 'Em 1988 foi criado o Sistema ﾃ嗜ico de Saﾃｺde (SUS), nosso sistema pﾃｺblico e universal de saﾃｺde. Apesar da sua importﾃ｢ncia na diminuiﾃｧﾃ｣o das disparidades em saﾃｺde, o sistema de saﾃｺde tem\nconsistentemente liderado a lista de maiores problemas do paﾃｭs segundo as pesquisas de\nopiniﾃ｣o. Reclamaﾃｧﾃｵes frequentes sobre o sistema privado tﾃｪm contribuﾃｭdo para a conclusﾃ｣o de que a saﾃｺde ﾃｩ um\nproblema generalizado no paﾃｭs. O uso de big data pode trazer melhorias\nsignificativas em termos de gestﾃ｣o, transparﾃｪncia e responsabilidade por parte dos\nprovedores de saﾃｺde, alﾃｩm de fornecer dados importantes para os pacientes. Este curso irﾃ｡ abordar tanto a obtenﾃｧﾃ｣o de dados em saﾃｺde como a sua utilizaﾃｧﾃ｣o para\nmelhorar a qualidade de tomada de decisﾃｵes por parte de hospitais e das diferentes esferas do governo. Mais especificamente, abordaremos as fontes de dados pﾃｺblicos de saﾃｺde, o uso do R e do Python para a\nanﾃ｡lise de dados, metodologias de big data (como machine learning, reduﾃｧﾃ｣o de\ndimensﾃ｣o e como evitar associaﾃｧﾃｵes espﾃｺrias), noﾃｧﾃｵes de economia da saﾃｺde e o uso de metodologias causais em pesquisas cientﾃｭficas.ﾂ�Apesar de o foco do curso ser a ﾃ｡rea da saﾃｺde, os conhecimentos podem ser diretamente aplicados em outras ﾃ｡reas como a educaﾃｧﾃ｣o, biologia, economia e administraﾃｧﾃ｣o. As aulas jﾃ｡ comeﾃｧaram e vocﾃｪ pode assistir normalmente a todo o conteﾃｺdo do curso independentemente do perﾃｭodo de inscriﾃｧﾃ｣o.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/bigdatabrasil', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=034b0750647811e598f05d7faad177e4', '2015-10-15', 6, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/2b/3cecc04c1711e58ddec752f068dbe2/Sem-t_tulo.png', 'Stats, Health', 'Coursera', 0, 'Portuguese', 'yes', 'Universidade de Sﾃ｣o Paulo', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(970, 'Live!:  A History of Art for Artists, Animators and Gamers', 'Explore art history from the artist''s perspective.  Learn how contemporary artists, animators and gamers work from the art of the past as part of their creative process, while building your own skills in visual analysis and creative and critical thinking.\n', 'This course approaches the questions of 窶彗rt窶� and 窶徂istory窶� from the perspective of contemporary makers of art (sculpture, painting, photography, performance, installation and more), animators (whether character/story-based or experimental) and gamers, asking how artists actively make a history for their own practices by thinking about the creative process as a 窶彡onversation窶� with a wide range of art from the past. Why are ground-breaking artists so often historically-minded (and yet tend to break all the rules of conventional history-telling)? How do animators themselves 窶忤rite窶� the largely unwritten history of their art through quotation, transposition and mash-ups? Why should contemporary gamers look at classical painting anyway?ﾂ�\n\n This course will combine short video lectures/interviews and interactive quizzes with independent, peer-reviewedﾂ�sketchbook and field work (suggested visits to local museums, film viewings, etc.) It is intended to give the student a background in a wide range of visual practices and a greater familiarity with techniques of historical analysis. It will help to build skills in visual analysis, and will also provide insight into the creative culture of CalArts, where a certain portion of these art histories have been made in the first place.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/livearthistory', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ym1rMrbVWtc', '2014-02-24', 9, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/bb/179ca240c8dc77cd68129d7d48e4ff/JEANNENE_P.jpg', 'Humanities , Arts, Music', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'California Institute of the Arts', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
