(985, 'Confronting The Big Questions: Highlights of Modern Astronomy', 'An introduction to modern astronomy''s most important questions. The four sections of the course are Planets and Life in The Universe; The Life of Stars; Galaxies and Their Environments; The History of The Universe.', 'This course provides students with a short overview of structure and content of the Universe. ﾂ�Each week will cover one question. ﾂ�In week one we address the issue of extra-solar planets - planets orbiting other stars and ask what do we know about these alien worlds touching on issues of life in the Universe as well. In the second week we explore the life of stars. ﾂ�The third week looks at galaxies their history and their distribution across space. ﾂ�The last two lectures explore cosmology - the history of the Universe as a whole.\n By the end of the class students will have gained an overview of the Universe they inhabit and an understanding of its biggest unresolved questions.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/astronomy', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IhdCu2OHtnc', '2014-02-23', 4, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/3e/462e5f6b7d94efa7e0f372760b1a2e/HighlightsAstronomyLogo-2.jpg', 'Physics', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Rochester', '2015-11-21 09:19:33'),
(986, 'Cloud Computing Concepts: Part 2', 'Learn core distributed computing concepts that underlie today窶冱 and tomorrow窶冱 cloud computing systems.', 'Cloud computing systems today, whether open-source or used inside companies, are built using a common set of core techniques, algorithms, and design philosophies窶蚤ll centered around distributed systems. Learn about such fundamental distributed computing "concepts" for cloud computing. \n\n Some of these concepts include:\n \n Clouds, MapReduce, key-value stores\n Classical precursors\n Widely-used algorithms\n Classical algorithms \n Scalability\n Trending areas\n And more! Understandﾂ�how these techniques workﾂ�inside today窶冱 most widely-used cloud computing systems. Get your hands dirty using these concepts with provided homework exercises. In theﾂ�optional programming track, implement some of these concepts in template assignments provided in C++ programming language. You will also watch interviews with leading managers and researchers, from both industry and academia.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/cloudcomputing2', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c9d85310639211e4a654d3e88b6ec309', '2015-03-16', 5, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/88/035dc0642f11e4be486baff3901205/cloud_computing_concepts_part02_v04_600X340.jpg', 'ComSci: Theory, ComSci: SE, Info, Tech, Engi', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(987, 'Innovaciﾃｳn educativa con recursos abiertos', 'Este curso promueve el conocimiento de los recursos educativos abiertos y su integraciﾃｳn en el movimiento educativo abierto, como una oportunidad para innovar en los procesos formativos a travﾃｩs de prﾃ｡cticas docentes innovadoras.', 'El curso cubre la temﾃ｡tica de la selecciﾃｳn, uso y reﾃｺso de recursos educativos abiertos, las posibilidades de repositorios que alojan estos materiales, estrategias de bﾃｺsqueda e integraciﾃｳn en procesos formativos, asﾃｭ como de valorar su mediciﾃｳn e impacto en los aprendizajes de los participantes. \n\nEl participante podrﾃ｡ desarrollar competencias digitales y de diseﾃｱo Instruccional para integrar recursos educativos abiertos (REA) en los ambientes de aprendizaje a travﾃｩs de prﾃ｡cticas educativas abiertas.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/innovacionrea', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YDNrn6ZqRLY', '2014-09-01', 4, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/2b/86ba2425aee6c8ab4307d2481f405e/imagen1_cursovladimir.png', 'Education', 'Coursera', 0, 'Spanish', 'yes', 'Tecnolﾃｳgico de Monterrey', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(988, 'Chinese Characters for beginner 豎牙ｭ�', 'Welcome to "Chinese Characters for beginner"!\nThis is an elementary course on learning Chinese characters. Together, we will start from the basic element of Chinese characters-- Strokes. Then we will learn 1,200 basic Chinese words composed of 240 commonly used Chinese characters, which begin with  窶應ｸ�窶�(one), including pronunciation, shape and meaning, so that to improve the learning effect. \n\nGood luck !', '"Chinese Characters for beginner" (1st volume) course\nwill be divided into 40 lessons in this term.There will be one lesson on every Monday\nto Thursday. Each lesson has a theme shown in a short video of 5-10 minutes.\nIn the video, there are 6 characters relevant to the theme. There are totally 240\nChinese characters in this course. After the teaching of the Chinese\ncharacters, the common Chinese vocabulary, which is composed of the Chinese\ncharacters taught in the previous part, will be shown in the second part of the\nvideo. In this way, the Chinese characters and the vocabulary could be combined\ntogether to enhance the learner`s reading ability. Each Friday will be a\nday of learners` self - testing. No lesson will be on that day, but a quiz\ninstead. The score of 70 out of 100 is required.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/chinesecharacters', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6b992900547311e5b22cb5fda6fb9b0b', '2015-10-08', 10, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/7a/726e00547311e5be2961689cf749f6/______1.jpg', 'Humanities', 'Coursera', 0, 'Chinese (PRC)', 'yes', 'Peking University', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(989, 'La visione del mondo della Relativitﾃ� e della Meccanica Quantistica', 'In questo corso imparerete i Principi che stanno alla base della Fisica del XX secolo, cioﾃｨ della Relativitﾃ� e la Meccanica Quantistica, e come sia cambiata la nostra visione del mondo.', 'La fisica del XX secolo, con le teorie della Relativitﾃ� e della Meccanica Quantistica, ha cambiato radicalmente la visione del mondo che ci circonda. Dallo spazio e tempo assoluti e indipendenti si ﾃｨ passati ad una descrizione di un mondo in cui distanze\ned intervalli di tempo dipendono da chi le osserva, in cui l窶冩rdine di accadimento di due eventi non ﾃｨ sempre univoco, in cui la velocitﾃ� del tempo segnato da un orologio dipende da quali corpi si trovino vicino. Nel microscopico si ﾃｨ invece abbandonata la descrizione\ndella fisica classica, magari caotica, ma sempre deterministica, per arrivare ad una descrizione probabilistica, in cui gli stati e le proprietﾃ� del mondo microscopico non sono determinati, a priori, intrinsecamente, ma acquisiscono realtﾃ� solo se vengano\nmisurati o se entrino in contatto con altri 窶徙ggetti窶�. L窶兮bbandono della realtﾃ� locale, del fatto cioﾃｨ che le azioni esercitate in un luogo, per particolari sistemi, possono avere effetti istantanei su oggetti a distanze virtualmente infinite, stravolge\nla descrizione di un mondo che fino al secolo scorso sembrava sensato e ragionevole. Nel corso verranno descritte le principali caratteristiche di queste due teorie, come abbiano cambiato il concetto del nostro universo e delle possibilitﾃ� di conoscerlo,\ne come abbiano influito nella vita quotidiana.\n', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/rqm', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c6-HjO4_WMU', '2014-03-10', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/db/331edd3f16a7391ffa670a6fefa03d/logo-RQM-4-1-liv.jpg', 'Humanities , Physics', 'Coursera', 0, 'Italian', 'yes', 'Sapienza University of Rome', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(990, 'Representaciones Culturales de las Sexualidades ', 'En este curso aprenderemos a interpretar cﾃｳmo se inscriben y materializan los discursos acerca del gﾃｩnero y la sexualidad en diversos productos y medios culturales (literatura, cine, televisiﾃｳn, fotografﾃｭa, internet, etc.). ', 'Desde los estudios de gﾃｩnero, los estudios queer y\nlos estudios culturales, este curso quiere familiarizar a los estudiantes con\nlas representaciones culturales de las sexualidades no normativas en la cultura\ncontemporﾃ｡nea. Planteamos diversos marcos teﾃｳricos y ejemplos prﾃ｡cticos a\npartir de los cuales reflexionar sobre las construcciones corporales e\nidentitarias de las personas lesbianas, gays, transgﾃｩnero, transexuales, queer,\nheterosexuales, etc. en diversos soportes culturales como el cine, la\nliteratura, internet, la televisiﾃｳn o las artes plﾃ｡sticas. De este modo,\nqueremos contribuir al anﾃ｡lisis de los discursos normativos sobre el gﾃｩnero y\nla sexualidad que nos construyen como sujetos y nos proporcionan posiciones\njerﾃ｡rquicas dentro del marco social. Entendemos que las representaciones\nculturales son espacios privilegiados para llevar a cabo este anﾃ｡lisis, porque\nen ellos se materializan tanto los discursos hegemﾃｳnicos como sus posibilidades\nde subversiﾃｳn. \n\n El contenido teﾃｳrico, siempre explicado a travﾃｩs del\nanﾃ｡lisis de obras artﾃｭsticas y productos culturales concretos, se estructura\nalrededor de cuatro unidades, repartidas en las cuatro semanas de duraciﾃｳn del\ncurso: representaciones, textualidad y corporalidades gﾃｩnero/s sexualidad/des cultura, identidad y comunidad \n\n El curso estﾃ｡ orientado a cualquier persona\ninteresada en la cultura, el gﾃｩnero y la sexualidad, sin necesidad de\nconocimientos previos. Queremos ofrecer contenidos sugestivos para aquellos\nestudiantes ya familiarizados con la temﾃ｡tica, sin descuidar las reflexiones y\nexplicaciones necesarias para aquellos que se adentran en ella por primera vez. Colaboradores \n\n Mireia Calafell Mayte Cantero Michelle Gamma Francisco Lazo Anna Orta Irina Sureda', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/representaciones', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4ZYO8eeLYRs', '2014-06-30', 4, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/cc/b013e0a51311e38271e5dfee787c94/logorepresentaciones5.jpg', 'Humanities , Arts', 'Coursera', 0, 'Spanish', 'yes', 'Universitat Autﾃｲnoma de Barcelona', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(991, 'Analyzing the Universe', 'Using publicly available data from NASA of actual satellite observations of astronomical  x-ray sources, we explore some of the mysteries of the cosmos, including neutron stars, black holes, quasars and supernovae.', 'Science is really not about looking up facts in an encyclopedia.ﾂ� It is a process that\nextends what we know into the realm of the unexplored.ﾂ� This can be\nexciting, certainly; to be able to sneak a peek at the Universe at its strange,\nawesome, cosmic best.ﾂ� But it is very different from your run-of-the-mill\nstandard 窶徼extbook窶� idea of science.ﾂ� Science is a social, human endeavor. And as human beings, we crave authenticity.ﾂ� We have seen the trappings of\nsociety, we act as if we have mastered technology, and yet we know that\nsomething is lacking.ﾂ� We have succumbed to the lure of Ebay, Facebook and\nAmazon (at least, I know I have!), and yet we remain unsatisfied at some primal level.ﾂ�\nIt窶冱 time to peel away the layers of glitzy imagery and use our machines to exploit their ultimate purpose: the capability toﾂ� process large amounts\nof data with instructions that we provide, in order to test our ideas about how\nthe Universe seems to behave.ﾂ� In short, to do Science.ﾂ� For the\nfirst time, it is possible for the interested student (and we are all\nstudents, especially those that have any claim to be considered\n窶徑earned窶� , such as the instructor!) to have this experience on-line. The subject matter for this course will be divided into two\nbroad components which will be interwoven in an interdisciplinary fashion. The first is a general introduction to the physics and astronomy\ninformation you will need to understand basic phenomena that occur in the realm\nof x-ray astrophysics; the second is the presentation of authentic satellite\ndata from various exciting types of x-ray sources, which you will analyze to\nbetter understand the working of the high-energy Universe in which we live.\nThere are no prerequisites for this course, other than high-school mathematics\n(algebra and trigonometry). I hope you will enjoy your experience in "Analyzing the Universe".', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/analyze', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VfSumhQblEM', '2015-09-14', 6, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/69/c0e0fa7afe31813d3322a2b3007937/supernova-black-hole.jpg', 'Physics', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Rutgers the State University of New Jersey', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(992, 'Planning & Design of Sanitation Systems and Technologies ', 'Learn more about how to plan for urban sanitation at city and local/community levels, different sanitation system and technology configurations and examples of successful and failed urban sanitation systems in low- and middle-income countries.\n', 'Sanitation is one of\nthe most off-track MDGs and progress in urban sanitation is proving especially\ndifficult to achieve. The traditional response for\nimproving urban sanitation is typically based on a master planning approach\nwhich has widely failed to meet the needs of low-income communities living in\nslums, who cannot afford to pay the expected charges for service improvements. In this course you will learn how to plan for affordable and context-specific\nsanitation solutions using some state-of-the-art sector planning tools and frameworks\nsuch as Sanitation 21, Community-Led Urban Environmental Sanitation (CLUES) and\nthe Sanitation Systems Approach. By using exercises and concrete examples,\nparticipants will learn how to choose appropriate sanitation systems and\ntechnologies for a variety of urban contexts.\n\n It is the 2nd MOOC of the series on "Sanitation, Water and Solid Waste for Development", which is an\ninitiative of Sandec/Eawag\nand EPFL.\nSandec/Eawag develops and offers the series as WHO\nCollaborating Centre. The dissemination is supported by UNESCO.ﾂ�The first MOOC of the series is entitled "Introduction\nto Household Water Treatment and Safe Storage". Version franﾃｧaise: Le cours en bref - Planification & design des systﾃｨmes et technologies d窶僊ssainissement', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/sanitation', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cbf40b70005b11e49807574f2695bc9f', '2014-10-13', 5, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/b3/2a27c0df5711e38659934c061c03b1/Water-Sanitation-v2.jpg', 'SocSci, Health', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'ﾃ営ole Polytechnique Fﾃｩdﾃｩrale de Lausanne', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(993, 'The Roosevelt Century', 'Who were Franklin, Eleanor, and Theodor Roosevelt? What values did they stand for? This course explores twentieth century US history through these three unique leaders. The 3Rs propelled the United States into a superpower. They changed the way we think about security, equality, and freedom. The Roosevelt Century takes you through their time, and connects it with our own', 'This course will be offered On Demand. Sign up here to be notified when we go live. Who were Franklin, Eleanor, and Theodor\nRoosevelt? What values did the three Roosevelts (3Rs) stand for? How did these\ntwo presidents and one first lady influence the world we live in? This course\nexplores twentieth century US history through these three unique leaders.ﾂ� The\n3Rs propelled the United States into a superpower. They were innovators,\ncampaigners, mobilisers, communicators, and transgressors of tradition. They\nchanged the way we think about security, equality, and freedom. They gave us\nimages of the future which still inspire us today. The Roosevelt Century takes\nyou through their time, and connects it with our own.ﾂ� By looking at their\npublic speeches, governing styles, leadership qualities, and major decisions,\nthe course explores how the 3Rs shaped American politics and society,\ntransformed the relationship between citizen and state, and changed the role of\nthe United States in the world.ﾂ� The legacy of the 3Rs can be found everywhere\nin public life today, from media and entertainment to place names and online\nsites. By linking these images and references to the past, participants will\ntake part in an exploration of the Roosevelt Century and how it is experienced\nacross the globe.ﾂ�', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/roosevelt', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c1203c70555311e5a16afd24e8547cc9', '2021-01-01', 0, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/97/315c40554f11e59ca9d3858f5380c9/Franklin-Roosevelt.jpg', 'Humanities', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Universiteit Leiden', '2015-11-21 09:19:34');
