(1017, 'Introducciﾃｳn a las Finanzas Corporativas', 'Este curso proporciona una breve introducciﾃｳn a los fundamentos de las finanzas. Puedes aplicar estas habilidades en un reto empresarial real como parte de la Programa Especializado de Fundamentos Empresariales de Wharton.', 'PARTE DE LA PROGRAMA ESPECIALIZADO DE FUNDAMENTOS EMPRESARIALES DE WHARTON Aquﾃｭ puedes ver como Geoffrey Garrett, Decano de Wharton School, habla sobre la Programa Especializado. Este curso proporciona el entorno, los conceptos y las herramientas para analizar decisiones financieras basadas en los principios fundamentales la teorﾃｭa moderna financiera. Aprenderﾃ｡s el lenguaje y los conceptos clave de la financiaciﾃｳn y la inversiﾃｳn empresarial incluyendo el cﾃ｡lculo de los valores actuales, la valoraciﾃｳn de bonos y acciones, la regla del VAN, mediciﾃｳn del riesgo, presupuesto del capital y el modelo de valoraciﾃｳn de activos financieros. Al final de este curso, serﾃ｡s capaz de leer, entender y explicar la gestiﾃｳn financiera empresarial y las decisiones de inversiﾃｳn.ﾂ� Completa este curso como parte de la Programa Especializado de Fundamentos Empresariales de Wharton, y tendrﾃ｡s la oportunidad de realizar el Proyecto Final y de preparar un anﾃ｡lisis estratﾃｩgico y proponer soluciones a un reto empresarial real de compaﾃｱﾃｭas dirigidas por Wharton como Televisa o a un reto al que se enfrente tu propia compaﾃｱﾃｭa u organizaciﾃｳn. Un equipo capacitado de Wharton evaluarﾃ｡ los mejores trabajos, y los equipos de liderazgo de Televisa revisarﾃ｡n los proyectos con mayor puntuaciﾃｳn elaborados para sus compaﾃｱﾃｭas.ﾂ� Mira este vﾃｭdeo para aprender mﾃ｡s sobre la Serie sobre Fundamentos de Wharton en Coursera:ﾂ� http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SgS3AJCe6i8 Para obtener mﾃ｡s informaciﾃｳn sobre los cursos online que ofrece Wharton, por favor visita online.wharton.upenn.edu', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/whartonfinancees', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ddd981c00fd811e5a54fa725ebdaaaa4', '2016-01-20', 4, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/b8/a6a0305e3a11e5adbc91778d679a31/whartonfinance.jpg', 'Bus & Mngmt', 'Coursera', 0, 'Spanish', 'yes', 'University of Pennsylvania', '2015-11-21 09:19:33'),
(1018, 'Foundations of E-Commerce ', 'The aim of this course is to understand issues that companies need to address when moving from being offline to online and learn how companies can craft business models where IT is embedded as an integral part of products, processes and customer interactions. You would get to appreciate how IT is changing the way companies create value through networks and coopetition.', 'This\nis a course about the fundamentals of the online/digital world.ﾂ� It窶冱 aim to provide a set of concepts and\ntools with which to view online developments.ﾂ�\nThese concepts are the language and the vocabulary which can explain and\nalso predict how technology impacts different industries. The\ncourse is not an overview of EC or IT developments but rather ways in which we\ncan make sense of EC and IT developments.ﾂ�\nThus, the emphasis is not on the 窶忤hat窶� but on the 窶忤hy.窶� In\nthe first 5 weeks, different concepts and their significance are explained. ﾂ�The role of these concepts in explaining the\nsuccess of dominant, marquee companies is also discussed. \n\n\n\n\n\n In\nthe 6th and final week, participants observe how these concepts apply\nto different contexts.ﾂ� These contexts\nare case studies of multiple companies. Actual class discussions are shown to\nillustrate how the concepts can be used to understand and predict IT-driven\ntransformations.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/ntuecom', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=09405b30fdd911e382b6a30696c0cfd2', '2015-01-19', 6, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/e7/ec7a603e0911e48eaa9f0838777cc3/E-Commerce-Course-Display_v1.1-01.png', 'Bus & Mngmt, Info, Tech', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Nanyang Technological University, Singapore', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(1019, 'Proyecto de Fundamentos Empresariales de Wharton', 'El Proyecto Final de Conocimiento Aplicado de Wharton te permite aplicar tus habilidades analﾃｭticas a retos de negocios reales, incluyendo el tuyo. Usarﾃ｡s esas habilidades empresariales recientemente adquiridas, para evaluar de manera reflexiva una oportunidad o situaciﾃｳn real de compaﾃｱﾃｭas dirigidas por Wharton como Televisa.', 'El Proyecto Final de Conocimiento Aplicado de Wharton te permite aplicar tus habilidades analﾃｭticas a retos de negocios reales, incluyendo el tuyo. Usarﾃ｡s esas habilidades empresariales recientemente adquiridas, para evaluar de manera reflexiva una oportunidad o situaciﾃｳn real de compaﾃｱﾃｭas dirigidas por Wharton como Televisa.Tambiﾃｩn podrﾃ｡s preparar un anﾃ｡lisis estratﾃｩgico y plantear una soluciﾃｳn a un reto al que se enfrente tu propia compaﾃｱﾃｭa u organizaciﾃｳn. Personal cualificado de Wharton evaluarﾃ｡ los mejores trabajos, y equipos de direcciﾃｳn de Televisa revisarﾃ｡n los proyectos que obtengan mejor puntuaciﾃｳn.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/whartoncapstonees', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=26926550b07811e48c1641d41061e90c', '2016-02-05', 4, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/97/004d205e4211e5812451eb2b63f9df/whartoncapstone.png', 'Bus & Mngmt', 'Coursera', 0, 'Spanish', 'yes', 'University of Pennsylvania', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(1020, 'Fundamentals of Digital Image and Video Processing', 'In this class you will learn the basic principles and tools used to process images and videos, and how to apply them in solving practical problems of commercial and scientific interests.  ', 'Digital images and videos are everywhere these days 窶� in thousands of\nscientific (e.g., astronomical, bio-medical), consumer, industrial, and\nartistic applications. Moreover they come in a wide range of the\nelectromagnetic spectrum - from visible light and infrared to gamma rays and\nbeyond. The ability to process image and video signals is therefore an\nincredibly important skill to master for engineering/science students, software\ndevelopers, and practicing scientists.ﾂ�ﾂ�\nDigital image and video processing continues to enable the multimedia\ntechnology revolution we are experiencing today. Some important examples of\nimage and video processing include the removal of degradations images suffer\nduring acquisition (e.g., removing blur from a picture of a fast moving car),\nand the compression and transmission of images and videos (if you watch videos\nonline, or share photos via a social media website, you use this everyday!),\nfor economical storage and efficient transmission.ﾂ�\n\nThis course will cover the fundamentals of image and video processing.ﾂ� We will provide a mathematical framework to describe and analyze images and videos as two- and three-dimensional signals in the spatial, spatio-temporal, and frequency domains. In this class not only will you learn the theory behind fundamental processing tasks including image/video enhancement, recovery, and compression - but you will also learn how to perform these key processing tasks in practice using state-of-the-art techniques and tools. We will introduce and use a wide variety of such tools 窶� from optimization toolboxes to statistical techniques. Emphasis on the special role sparsity plays in modern image and video processing will also be given.ﾂ� In all cases, example images and videos pertaining to specific application domains will be utilized.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/digital', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y1566JpskAI', '2015-03-30', 12, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/3e/8166be0abcc2a8803d91b7aa55135c/logo_aggelos.jpg', 'ComSci: AI, Info, Tech, Engi', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Northwestern University', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
