(1185, 'Practical Learning Analytics', 'Everyone in education has questions 窶� Practical Learning Analytics is about answering them. To be practical, we窶冤l focus on data every university records; to keep things interesting, we窶冤l examine questions raised by many audiences; to ensure impact, we窶冤l provide realistic data and example code. ', 'Everyone involved in higher\neducation has questions. Students want to know how they窶决e doing and which\nclasses they should take. Faculty members want to understand their students窶兔nbackgrounds and to learn whether their teaching techniques are effective. Staff\nmembers want to be sure the advice they provide is appropriate and find out whether\ncollege requirements accomplish their goals. Administrators want to explore how\nall of their students and faculty are doing and to anticipate emerging changes.\nThe public wants to know what happens in college and why.\n\n Everyone has questions. We have\nthe chance to help them find answers. \n\n Learning analytics is about using\ndata to improve teaching and learning. You might wonder why there窶冱 suddenly so\nmuch conversation about this previously invisible topic.[1] After\nall, institutions of higher education have maintained careful records of\nstudent progress and outcomes for more than a century. ﾂ�They have always been ready to provide a\ntranscript for every student, reporting all courses taken, grades received,\nhonors awarded, and degrees conferred. Institutional research offices provide\nsummaries of these student records to campus leaders, accreditation agencies,\nand the public. Why learning analytics now?\n\n Two major trends drive the\ncurrent emergence of learning analytics. First, data informing teaching and\nlearning are increasingly extensive and accessible. Second, innovative new analytic\napproaches to digesting, visualizing, and acting on these data emerge every day. What窶冱 special about this\ncourse? Practical Learning Analytics has a specific goal: to help us\ncollectively ponder learning analytics in a concrete way. To keep it practical,\nwe will focus on using traditional student record data, the kinds of data every\ncampus already has. To make it interesting, we will address questions raised by\nan array of different stakeholders, including campus leaders, faculty, staff,\nand especially students. To provide analytic teeth, each analysis we discuss\nwill be supported by both realistic data and sample code. Who should take this course? Practical Learning Analytics should provide something for anyone\ninterested in higher education: current, former, or future students, policy\nmakers, academic advisors, data scientists, university administrators, ed-tech\nentrepreneurs, faculty members, even the curious public. This course has been designed to\nwork for a wide variety of audiences. Its structure is modeled on something\neveryone can enjoy: a smﾃｶrgﾃ･sbord 窶貼nwe窶决e going to treat the class like one big meal. After we set the table, each\nguest may wander the room, taking either a small plate or a full entrﾃｩe from a\nseries of courses we offer up. When everyone is full, we窶冤l gather again over\ncoffee to hear what people thought. There is no defined way to pursue such a\nmeal 窶� each diner chooses what窶冱 right for them. And there is no defined way to\ntake this course 窶� every student must choose what窶冱 right for them. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n The course will open with a two\nweek introduction, exploring the landscape of learning analytics in higher\neducation and setting the table for the main event. This is followed by a four\nweek meal during which participants may choose among an array of five different\ntopics, each presented at two levels: a small plate providing a quick\nintroduction, or a more filling entrﾃｩe. Those choosing small plates will still have\nthe opportunity to work with realistic data, analyzing it with code we provide.\nThose choosing entrﾃｩes will make creative contributions of their own: writing\nnew code for analysis or visualization of the data we provide, perhaps bringing\nin data of their own. After this month of exploration, the final two weeks will\nfeature a concluding coffee. In them, we窶冤l review what students learned while\nwandering through all five courses, share the best things class members\ninvented, and provide some concluding remarks. \n\n\n\n\n\n \n\n [1]\nTry searching for 窶徑earning\nanalytics窶� in the Google Ngram server窶ｦnothing comes up!\n\n\n\n', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/pla', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6dc2045066ba11e5b4dda39037686940', '2015-10-05', 8, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/cd/cc2f30477311e59cabebd10e8caa4e/practicallearning.png', 'Education, Stats, Teach, Info, Tech', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Michigan', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(1186, 'Nanotechnology and Nanosensors', 'Learn about novel sensing tools that make use of nanotechnology to screen, detect and monitor various events in personal or professional life. Together, we will lay the groundwork for infinite innovative applications, starting from diagnosis and treatments of diseases, continuing with quality control of goods and environmental aspects, and ending with monitoring security issues. ', 'Nanotechnology and nanosensors are broad, interdisciplinary areas\nthat encompass (bio)chemistry, physics, biology, materials science, electrical\nengineering and more. The present course will provide a survey on some of the\nfundamental principles behind nanotechnology and nanomaterials and their vital\nrole in novel sensing properties and applications. The course will discuss interesting interdisciplinary\nscientific and engineering knowledge at the nanoscale to understand fundamental\nphysical differences at the nanosensors. By the end of the course, students\nwill understand the fabrication, characterization, and manipulation of\nnanomaterials, nanosensors, and how they can be exploited for new applications.\nAlso, students will apply their knowledge of nanotechnology and nanosensors to\na topic of personal interest in this course.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/nanosensors', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HTqLKe4_j-c', '2015-03-16', 10, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/8a/1cd9dcb449398aa92ad305413d1b91/sensor-1.jpg', 'Bio & Life Sci, Chem, Engi', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Technion - Israel Institute of Technology', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(1187, 'Bajemos la temperatura - Por quﾃｩ se debe evitar un planeta 4ﾂｰC mﾃ｡s cﾃ｡lido', 'Es evidente que si no tomamos medidas para combatir el cambio climﾃ｡tico el mundo serﾃ｡ 4 grados centﾃｭgrados mﾃ｡s cﾃ｡lido a finales de siglo. Este incremento de temperatura amenaza nuestra sociedad tras dﾃｩcadas de desarrollo y nos encontramos actualmente en un punto de inflexiﾃｳn decisivo para el futuro de la humanidad. Este curso presenta las ﾃｺltimas evidencias cientﾃｭficas sobre el cambio climﾃ｡tico y algunas de las alternativas e iniciativas que debemos empezar a implementar lo antes posible para poder revertir la situaciﾃｳn.', 'Dados los compromisos existentes, es probable que el mundo se vea abocado a un calentamiento de 4 grados centﾃｭgrados para finales de este siglo y de 2 grados centﾃｭgrados para el 2040. Este curso en lﾃｭnea masivo y abierto, MOOC (por sus siglas en inglﾃｩs), reﾃｺne a cientﾃｭficos de renombre con el fin de proporcionar un resumen de las pruebas cientﾃｭficas mﾃ｡s recientes y presentar un anﾃ｡lisis de los posibles futuros impactos y riesgos, centrﾃ｡ndose en los paﾃｭses en vﾃｭas de desarrollo. El curso ofrece una crﾃｳnica histﾃｳrica de los cambios observados en el sistema climﾃ｡tico y sus impactos, su relaciﾃｳn con el aumento de las emisiones de diﾃｳxido de carbono, las correspondientes subidas de la temperatura, el deshielo de los glaciares y los cambios en los patrones de precipitaciﾃｳn. Este curso tambiﾃｩn ofrece diferentes proyecciones que vaticinan un aumento de las sequﾃｭas, olas de calor y subidas del nivel del mar a lo largo del siglo XXI, con sus implicaciones para la seguridad alimentaria y la seguridad del agua, asﾃｭ como los posibles impactos en la agricultura, la disponibilidad de agua, los ecosistemas y la salud humana.\n \n Este MOOC presenta un anﾃ｡lisis de los impactos derivados del eventual calentamiento del planeta de 4 grados centﾃｭgrados y hace hincapiﾃｩ en la necesidad de que tanto los responsables polﾃｭticos como las comunidades se planteen seriamente sus opciones de adaptaciﾃｳn al cambio climﾃ｡tico, recalcando la necesidad de tomar medidas de mitigaciﾃｳn de forma urgente. Los participantes tambiﾃｩn tendrﾃ｡n la oportunidad de comprender los riesgos que implica alcanzar puntos de inflexiﾃｳn irreversibles, como la desintegraciﾃｳn del manto de hielo de la Antﾃ｡rtica occidental o la muerte y retroceso a gran escala de la selva Amazﾃｳnica. El curso termina con un debate sobre las principales opciones y alternativas polﾃｭticas existentes y necesarias para prevenir un calentamiento superior a 2 grados centﾃｭgrados. \n \nEn el caso de Latinoamﾃｩrica, las temperaturas extremadamente elevadas y los patrones cambiantes de las precipitaciones tendrﾃ｡n efectos adversos en la productividad agrﾃｭcola, los regﾃｭmenes hidrolﾃｳgicos y la biodiversidad. En Brasil, un calentamiento de 2 grados centﾃｭgrados podrﾃｭa disminuir el rendimiento de los cultivos hasta un 70 por ciento en el caso de la soja y hasta un 50 por ciento en el caso del trigo para el aﾃｱo 2050. La acidificaciﾃｳn de los ocﾃｩanos, la subida del nivel del mar, los ciclones tropicales y los cambios de temperatura afectarﾃ｡n enormemente a los hﾃ｡bitats costeros, el turismo, la salud y la seguridad alimentaria e hﾃｭdrica. Ademﾃ｡s, el deshielo de los glaciares supondrﾃｭa un peligro para las ciudades andinas. La economﾃｭa podrﾃｭa verse duramente perjudicada a causa del cambio climﾃ｡tico, afectando irremediablemente a la sociedad en general y a los mﾃ｡s desfavorecidos en particular. Para el aﾃｱo 2050, si se produjera un calentamiento de 4 grados centﾃｭgrados en la regiﾃｳn de Amﾃｩrica Latina, las inundaciones costeras y las tormentas podrﾃｭan causar pﾃｩrdidas de unos 22 000 millones de dﾃｳlares, relacionadas esencialmente con daﾃｱos a las infraestructuras y con pﾃｩrdidas en el sector turﾃｭstico.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/bajemostemperatura', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ba762e30d19f11e483bcaf7da52ce995', '2016-06-20', 5, 'https://d15cw65ip