(1218, 'American Health Policy: The Structure of the American Health Care System (Part I of II)', 'This course will explain the structure of the American health care system and explore the many problems of this complicated system. Part I of II.', 'The American health care system has many problems. 50 million people are uninsured. Quality is extremely uneven, with peaks of greatness at leading academic centers but overall poor quality in both process measures and outcomes such as asthma deaths. Finally, the U.S. health care system spends over $8000 per patient per year, nearly double the next highest country. In March 2010, the Affordable Care Act was enacted. Over the next decade or more, the Act will dramatically re-structure the American health care system. Part I of this course will explore the history and structure of the current American health care system, including the history of and problems with employment-based health insurance, the challenges surrounding access, cost and quality, and the medical malpractice conundrum. It will conclude with the history of health care reform, leading up to the Affordable Care Act. Throughout lessons regarding health economics, health policy, and medical practice will be elucidated. Part II of this course will then explore the challenges that were overcome to achieve health reform in America. We will delineate the specific ways that the Affordable Care Act improves access and quality and will control costs. Part II will conclude with predictions about further reforms and about the future of health care in America.ﾂ� This class is open to anyone that is interested in gaining a better understanding of the US health care system and the challenges of health care reform. There are no prerequisites or required knowledge of the health system. Students who feel as though they have a strong grasp of the structure of the current US health system and the history of health care reform in the US may start with Part II of the course instead.ﾂ�', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/americanhealthsystem', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7aeceaf0b94011e497005baa633b4a79', '2015-03-23', 4, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/1d/d6f630b94011e4ba7cd57580ecf065/AmericanFlag_Stethoscope.jpg', 'Econ & Fin, Health', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Pennsylvania', '2015-11-21 09:19:33'),
(1219, 'American Health Policy: The Affordable Care Act and the Future of Health Care Reform (Part II of II)', 'This course will explore the Affordable Care Act in depth and then turn towards future health reform efforts and the future of the American health care system. Part II of II.', 'The American health care system has many problems. 50 million people are uninsured. Quality is extremely uneven, with peaks of greatness at leading academic centers but overall poor quality in both process measures and outcomes such as asthma deaths. Finally, the U.S. health care system spends over $8000 per patient per year, nearly double the next highest country. In March 2010, the Affordable Care Act was enacted. Over the next decade or more, the Act will dramatically re-structure the American health care system. This course will explore the challenges that were overcome to achieve health reform in America. We will delineate the specific ways that the Affordable Care Act improves access and quality, and will control costs. It will conclude with predictions about further reforms and about the future of health care in America.ﾂ� This class is open to anyone interested in gaining a better understanding of the Affordable Care Act and possible future health care reforms. While not required, we recommend you first take Part I of this course for background knowledge about the American health care system. Students who feel as though they have a strong grasp of the structure of the current US health system and the history of health care reform in the US may start with Part II.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/ushealthcarereform', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3ad10890bec511e4934039ff173e6d5a', '2015-05-04', 6, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/cb/604ca0b94711e4a23bb98819bc7a78/Health_Care_Reform.jpg', 'Econ & Fin, Health', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Pennsylvania', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(1220, 'Villes africaines: Introduction ﾃ� la planification urbaine / African cities : an introduction to urban planning', 'Le cours permet d''apprendre les bases de la planification urbaine ﾃ� travers ses dimensions techniques, environnementales, sociales et ﾃｩconomiques.\n\nThis course teaches the basics of the urban planning through its technical, environmental, societal and economical dimensions.', 'Nouveautﾃｩ!!! Le coursﾂ�窶弖illes africaines" permet d''acquﾃｩrir une Attestation de rﾃｩussite EPFL et 3 crﾃｩdits ECTS, il fait dﾃｩsormais partie du "Certificat d''ﾃｩtudes en gestion et planification de la ville africaine". Pour obtenir les crﾃｩdits , il faut suivre le cours, obtenir l''attestation en ligne et passer un examen final dans un des 37 centres de l''Agence Universitaire de la Francophonie (AUF) ﾃ� travers le monde. Les modalitﾃｩs d''inscription seront donnﾃｩes dans les premiﾃｨres semaines du cours Objectifs Le cours propose une\nintroduction ﾃ� la planification urbaine des villes africaines. Aprﾃｨs un\npassage par les grandes thﾃｩmatiques urbaines (changement climatique, ﾃｩnergie,\ndroit ﾃ� la ville, foncier, habitat 窶ｦ), nous aborderons les outils actuellement\nutilisﾃｩs en planification nous en feront une lecture critique. Nous\nverrons ensuite comment planifier une ville "intﾃｩgrative", ouverte,\nrespectueuse de l窶册nvironnement et faiblement consommatrice en ressources. Parallﾃｨlement, nous aborderons\nla question du financement des villes, le jeu des acteurs (gouvernance) et l窶凖ｩvaluation des planifications. L窶册ntrﾃｩe du cours n窶册st\npas disciplinaire, mais thﾃｩmatique. Le cours articule les niveaux de lecture de la\nville (technique, social et symbolique) aussi bien que les thﾃｩmatiques urbaines\npermettant de mettre en exergue les processus de fabrication de la ville. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n News !!!\n\n With the course "African Cities" you\ncan now acquire a certificate and 3 ECTS credits. The course is also part of\nthe "Certificate of Advanced Studies in Management and planning of the\nAfrican city."ﾂ�\n\n To receive credits, you must follow the\ncourse, obtain the State of accomplishment online and pass a final exam in one\nof the 70 centers of the Agence Universitaire de la Francophonie (AUF)\nworldwide.\n\n ﾂ�Registration details will be given in the\nfirst weeks of the course\n\n The course suggests an introduction to urban planning of African\ncities. After a short overview of the big urban issues (climate change, energy,\nright to the city, land, habitat窶ｦ), we will tackle the tools currently used in\nplanning and will have a critical reading. We will then see how to plan an\nintegrative, open, environmental-friendly and low-resource-consumption city.\n\n In parallel, we will approach the funding of the cities, the\ngovernance and the assessment of the planning.\n\n The approach of the course is not disciplinary, rather thematic.\nThe course articulates the different reading levels of the city (technical,\nsocial and symbolic) as well as urban issues allowing to highlight the making of a city.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/villesafricaines', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l1S8MKw5CrU', '2015-02-16', 12, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/58/8badd2362fcf15963865c12a200f9f/Villes-Africaines-v1.jpg', 'SocSci, Humanities', 'Coursera', 0, 'French', 'yes', 'ﾃ営ole Polytechnique Fﾃｩdﾃｩrale de Lausanne', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(1221, 'Nudge-it: Understanding obesity', 'Nudge-it is an multi-disciplinary European research project studying new ways of establishing and reinforcing healthy eating habits. Join us to learn about eating, appetite and obesity.', 'Obesity is a huge health, social and economic problem affecting millions\n of people globally. Currently, it窶冱 a problem without a solution - \ndieting is difficult, drug therapies are poor, and surgical solutions are \nonly offered to those suffering serious ill-health. In addition, there \nare many common misconceptions about appetite, diet and exercise, and about the\n best ways to treat or prevent obesity. \n \nThis course is taught by partners in the EU-funded research project Nudge-it.\n This project brings together dozens of experts in neurobiology, psychology andﾂ�behavioural economics from universities in the UK, Germany, \nthe Netherlands, Sweden, Switzerland, Denmark, the US and New Zealand. \nThe project''s overall aim is to better understand decision-making in food choice \nand to contribute to improving public health policy. \n \nIn this course we discuss the facts and misconceptions around \nobesity, and the gaps in the scientific knowledge. We discuss key \nphysiological and psychological concepts around the brain窶冱 control of \nappetite and body weight, and reflect on the power of these systems - \nhow they make weight gain easy and weight loss hard. We describe \nnew approaches to the treatment and prevention of obesity, and give you \nthe opportunity to reflect on your own knowledge and assumptions around \nthe causes of obesity. If you窶决e on Twitter, tell us why you are taking\nthe course 窶� use the hashtag #nudgeitmooc Visit the project website atﾂ�www.nudge-it.eu We''re on Twitter:ﾂ�@nudgeit_', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/nudgeit', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=20eb3c10557511e596bd717c099b28bf', '2015-10-05', 5, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/6b/142cf0c32811e4b15ef542c4021c58/nudgeitlogo_scaled.png', 'Bio & Life Sci, Econ & Fin, Medicine, Health, Nutrit', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'The University of Edinburgh', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(1222, 'Preparing for the AP* Calculus AB and BC Exams', 'This six week course will help students prepare for the AP* Calculus AB Exam.\n\n* AP Calculus is a registered trademark of the College Board, which was not involved in the production of, and does not endorse, this product.', 'This course reviews the topics for the AP Calculus AB Exam.ﾂ�Each weekﾂ�of the six week review will include review videos for an important block of material, complete withﾂ�videos of worked example problems and exam tips. There will also be an extensiveﾂ�online quiz given each week, with multiple problem versions that students can use to practice, along with an practice tests to help students prepare for the AP* Calculus AB Exam. * AP Calculus is a registered trademark of the College Board, which was not involved in the production of, and does not endorse, this product.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/apcalc', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iCaBB6RxJSY', '2015-03-16', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/5d/bca190749111e3bea989765a5f4524/calc_mooc_image.png', 'Math', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Houston System', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(1223, 'Women in Leadership: Inspiring Positive Change', 'This course aims to inspire and empower women and men across the world to engage in purposeful career development and take on leadership for important causes窶杯o lead change with more conviction and confidence窶蚤nd improve our workplaces and communities for all. ', 'This course aims to inspire and empower women and men across the world to engage in purposeful career development and take on leadership for important causes窶杯o learn the skills of leadership and lead change with more conviction and confidence窶蚤nd improve our workplaces and communities for all. ﾂ�By offering more complex understandings of issues related to professional women and work, the course will help you increase self-knowledge about your own values and vision, as well as enhance your capabilities as a leader, manager, and team contributor. ﾂ�We will examine the opportunities, challenges, trade-offs, and organizational dynamics experienced by women in work organizations, as well as reflect on and practice effective individual behaviors. The course aims at answering questions such as: What are the valued attributes and behaviors of women in the workplace? ﾂ�How does the gendered nature of organizations impact women? ﾂ�What derails our career advancement and what propels us upward? ﾂ�What are your leadership goals and aspirations? ﾂ�How can you best integrate your multiple family and work life commitments? How do you define career success? What can organizations do to provide women with opportunities to excel? ﾂ�What opportunities could our global economy harness by advancing women to leadership? ﾂ�How can the full talents of the workforce be tapped into and developed? ﾂ�', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/womeninleadership', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b42e59f0da2111e48895cb8328ae422f', '2016-01-04', 5, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/da/edc890c8c011e4b20e010433ef8142/iStock_000001528952Medium.jpg', 'Education, SocSci, Bus & Mngmt', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Case Western Reserve University', '2015-11-21 09:19:35'),
(1224, 'Statistical Mechanics: Algorithms and Computations', 'In this course you will learn a whole lot of modern physics (classical and quantum) from basic computer programs that you will download, generalize, or write from scratch, discuss, and then hand in. Join in if you are curious (but not necessarily knowledgeable) about algorithms, and about the deep insights into science that you can obtain by the algorithmic approach.', 'This\n course discusses the computational approach in modern physics in a \nclear yet accessible way. Individual modules contain in-depth \ndiscussions of algorithms ranging from basic enumeration methods to cutting-edge Markov-chain techniques. Emphasis will be put on \napplications in classical and quantum physics.ﾂ�Theﾂ�focus\n will be on subjects such as Monte Carlo sampling, molecular \ndynamics, transition phases in hard-sphere liquids, simulated annealing \nfor solving geometrical constraints, perfect sampling of classical spin \nmodels, to aspects of quantum Monte Carlo algorithms, Bose-Einstein \ncondensation, and many-body physics with fermions.ﾂ�The emphasis is on orientation. Discussion of implementation details will be kept to a minimum.\n \nThe course is entirely\nself-contained. It heavily relies on concise algorithmsﾂ� (each\nwith between 10 andﾂ� 50 lines of Python code). Modules lead from\nelementary discussions to the rich and difficult problems in\ncontemporary physics, and are of interest to a wide range of students\nin the natural sciences.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/smac', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j-Y4ogZNr_I', '2015-02-02', 10, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/13/8c315232b22ca1039266092dfb11dc/mooc_statistical_mechanics_2609.png', 'Math, Chem, ComSci: Theory, Physics', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'ﾃ営ole normale supﾃｩrieure', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(1225, 'Making Better Group Decisions: Voting, Judgement Aggregation and Fair Division', 'Learn about different voting methods and fair division algorithms, and explore the problems that arise when a group of people need to make a decision.  ', '\n			 \n				 \n					 Much of our daily life is spent taking part in various types of what we might call 窶徘olitical窶拿nprocedures. Examples range from voting in a national election to deliberating with others\nin small committees. Many interesting philosophical and mathematical issues arise when\nwe carefully examine our group decision-making processes.ﾂ� There are two types of group\ndecision making problems that we will discuss in this course. A voting problem: Suppose\nthat a group of friends are deciding where to go for dinner. If everyone agrees on which\nrestaurant is best, then it is obvious where to go. But, how should the friends decide where\nto go if they have different opinions about which restaurant is best? Can we always find a\nchoice that is 窶彷air窶� taking into account everyone窶冱 opinions or must we choose one person\nfrom the group to act as a 窶彭ictator窶�? A fair division problem: Suppose that there is a cake and\na group of hungry children. Naturally, you want to cut the cake and distribute the pieces\nto the children as fairly as possible. If the cake is homogeneous (e.g., a chocolate cake with\nvanilla icing evenly distributed), then it is easy to find a fair division: give each child a piece\nthat is the same size. But, how do we find a 窶彷air窶� division of the cake if it is heterogeneous\n(e.g., icing that is 1/3 chocolate, 1/3 vanilla and 1/3 strawberry) and the children each want\ndifferent parts of the cake?ﾂ�\n				\n			\n		', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/votingfairdiv', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KOEVQ_2fmIQ', '2014-09-01', 7, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/c9/68becd69bfac902edd2ea292619756/coursera_decisions.png', 'Math, Humanities , Econ & Fin, ComSci: AI', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Maryland, College Park', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(1226, 'Statistical Thermodynamics: Molecules to Machines', 'Thermodynamics explains phenomena we observe in the natural world and is the cornerstone of all of engineering. You''re going to learn about thermodynamics from a molecular picture where we''ll combine theory with a wide range of practical applications and examples. The principles you''ll learn in this class will help you understand energy systems such as batteries, semiconductors, catalysts from a molecular perspective.  But be warned: this is a fast-paced, challenging course. Everyone is welcome, but hold on to your hat! ', 'Modern engineering research focuses on designing new materials and processes at the molecular level. Statistical thermodynamics provides the formalism for understanding how molecular interactions lead to the observed collective behavior at the macroscale.ﾂ� This course will develop a molecular-level understanding of key thermodynamic quantities like heat, work, free energy and entropy. These concepts will be applied in understanding several important engineering and biological applications.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/stathermo', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d57096a0d4cc11e4b6e3875cd24c570f', '2015-04-20', 6, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/a5/aff3a0ce4311e49136915d63055160/logo_notitle.png', 'Chem, Energy & Earth Sci, Physics, Engi', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'null', '2015-11-21 09:19:34'),
(1227, 'Subsistence Marketplaces', 'Gain knowledge about subsistence marketplaces and use it in different parts of the world to make a difference. The broader aim of this course is for you to consider the global challenge of poverty and envision a better world by designing solutions based on sound understanding. ', '\n The foundation for this course lies with unique synergies between pioneering research, teaching, and social initiatives through the Subsistence Marketplaces Initiative. Unique to this approach is a bottom-up understanding of the intersection of poverty and the marketplace.\n\n The goals of this course are to help you develop an understanding of marketplace activity in the radically different context of subsistence where much of humanity resides and survives, and for you to design solutions that can be implemented by individuals, businesses, and social enterprises through economically, ecologically, and socially sustainable products for subsistence marketplaces.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/subsistence', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VEXsMlIy7z4', '2015-01-12', 8, 'https://coursera-course-photos.s3.amazonaws.com/04/46e780ec21c119523ae855e1dee768/Madhu_coursera_thumbnail_v2.jpg', 'Bus & Mngmt', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(1228, 'Introduction to Acoustics (Part 2)', 'Learn about acoustics by using the concept of impedance. Following part 1, radiation, scattering, and diffraction are studied. Wave propagation in closed space is also covered. Leads to understand essentials as well to cover graduate level topics. ', 'This course introduces acoustics by using the concept of impedance. In the previous part, the course starts with vibrations and waves, demonstrating how vibration can be envisaged as a kind of wave, mathematically and physically. They are realized by one-dimensional examples, which provide mathematically simplest but clear enough physical insights. Then the part 1 ends with explaining waves on a flat surface of discontinuity, demonstrating how propagation characteristics of waves change in space where there is a distributed impedance mismatch.ﾂ� Following the part 1, part 2 starts with radiation, scattering, and diffraction, which can be explained in a unified way by seeing the changes of waves due to spatially distributed impedance. Lastly, the course covers sound in closed space, which is considered to be a space that is surrounded by spatially distributed impedance, and introduces two spaces: acoustically large and small space.ﾂ� This course is for graduate students and advanced undergraduates in acoustics, audio engineering, and noise control engineering. Practicing engineers and researchers in audio engineering and noise control, or students in engineering and physics disciplines, who want to gain an understanding sound and vibration concepts, are also welcome. For the continuity of the lecture, taking part 1 of the course is recommended (but not required).ﾂ�', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/acoustics2', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=db052c00a04e11e480629fd0b8fc278f', '2015-08-24', 5, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/09/77d4500b1e11e490260f44f72551be/05.gif', 'Music, Physics, Engi', 'Coursera', 0, 'English', 'yes', 'Korea Advanced Institute of Science and Technology', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
(1229, 'Initiation ﾃ� la programmation (en C++)', 'Ce cours initie ﾃ� la programmation en utilisant le langage C++. Il ne prﾃｩsuppose pas de connaissance prﾃｩalable. Les aspects plus avancﾃｩs (programmation orientﾃｩe objet) sont donnﾃｩs dans un cours suivant, ﾂｫIntroduction ﾃ� la programmation orientﾃｩe objet (en C++)ﾂｻ.', 'Ce cours prﾃｩsente des concepts de base de la programmation tels queﾂ�ﾂ� : variables, expressions, structures de contrﾃｴle, fonctions/mﾃｩthodes, ... en les illustrant dans la syntaxe du langage C++. Ces notions simples seront pratiquﾃｩes de faﾃｧon intensive pour vous faire rﾃｩaliser de faﾃｧon de plus en plus autonomeﾂ� les ﾃｩtapes allant de la conception d''un programme (algorithme) ﾃ� sa mise en oeuvre concrﾃｨte. Ce cours est conﾃｧu pour ﾃｪtre prolongﾃｩ par les aspects orientﾃｩ-objet, prﾃｩsentﾃｩs dans le coursﾂ�ﾂ�ﾂｫIntroduction ﾃ� la programmation orientﾃｩe objet (en C++)ﾂｻ.ﾂ�', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/initprogcpp', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ea31a4700dae11e49b9e39d20e021070', '2015-09-18', 8, 'https://d15cw65ipctsrr.cloudfront.net/c0/da50f005b511e4af5851f2b4eaa998/Init-C__-final.jpg', 'ComSci: SE', 'Coursera', 0, 'French', 'yes', 'ﾃ営ole Polytechnique Fﾃｩdﾃｩrale de Lausanne', '2015-11-21 09:19:36'),
